title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese; place into large casserole dish.
Cover with large amount of American cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 300° for about 1 hour or until cheese is melted.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Saute green pepper strips in hot oil until tender.
Remove and set aside.
Season meat with salt and pepper and brown on both sides in oil.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, wine, garlic and green peppers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and apple.
Stir well.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Keeps for a long time.

title: shrimp stew
directions: In 6 to 8-quart pot, heat oil and stir in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until a medium brown roux is formed, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Lower heat and add chopped onion, shallots, celery and garlic.
Stir thoroughly and cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper, cayenne, bay leaves, thyme and mix well.
Add chopped tomatoes, water and lemon juice, then simmer 1 hour, stirring frequently. Add the cubed potatoes and simmer for 10 minutes longer.
Add the shrimp; cover the pot and simmer over low heat for 25 minutes.

title: cheesy taters
directions: In large bowl, mix peeled, sliced potatoes and margarine. Spread half of the potatoes in a baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 cheese.
Add more potatoes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 15 minutes more until potatoes are tender.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean when inserted in center of pie.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Store in jars in refrigerator.
Very good with greens.

title: three cheesy lasagne
directions: Prepare lasagne as directed.
Stir in creamed cottage cheese and grated Parmesan cheese.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese. Cover and heat over low heat until melted, 3 to 5 minutes. Garnish with tomatoes, parsley and ripe olives.

title: corned beef and green onion cheese ball
directions: Cut corned beef into small bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Mold into 2 balls.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Serve with crackers.

title: mock lobster salad
directions: Boil haddock until done.
Let cool, then flake.
Mix with celery, olives, onion, pimento and chopped lettuce.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Garnish with lettuce and olives.

title: european rabbit
directions: Mix salt, pepper and flour; flour rabbit.
Melt butter; brown rabbit.
Place in a roaster.
Add the melted butter, water, onions and remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot!!! salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: "easy french recipe"
directions: Combine all ingredients, except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add to the mixture.
Grease a pan 20 cm.
wide.
Pour in pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve lukewarm or cold with pudding or a little jam.
Decorate if you wish.

title: pasta with carbonara sauce
directions: Eggs, butter or margarine and cream must be room temperature. Beat together the eggs and cream until blended.
Cook pasta 10 to 12 minutes in boiling, salted water; drain well.
Turn pasta into a preheated 250° ovenproof serving dish.
Toss pasta with butter and pepperoni.
Pour egg mixture over and toss.
Add cheese and parsley; toss to mix.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: baked penne rigate
directions: Boil penne rigate and drain.
In a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan line bottom with small amount of sauce.
Put all ingredients in pan one by one, gently and thoroughly, mixing with penne rigate. Stir in remaining sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pancakes or waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Beat egg and add milk;
stir into dry ingredients.
Add butter.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill until time to serve.

title: pink chiffon fruit dip
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix well.
Stir in food coloring.
Serve with fresh fruit, vanilla wafers or graham crackers.

title: buttermilk bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon; reserve drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Stir buttermilk and bacon drippings into sour cream; blend well. Add onion, seasonings and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Serve over tossed green salad. Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: shrimp stir-fry
directions: *Carrots, green peppers and green onions are good.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter in 2-quart saucepan; bring to boil.
Beat eggs; pour over hot syrup and beat while pouring.
To make a real pecan pie, add about 3 cups of chopped pecans and mix. Add vanilla; pour in crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until the crust is browned just right.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Saute ham, onions and hot sauce in oil over moderate heat for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently until the onions are soft but not browned.
Combine black-eyed peas, ham mixture and rice, then heat.
Garnish with chopped pimento and green onion.

title: mushroom spread
directions: Saute mushrooms, chopped onion and butter in pan until liquid evaporates.
In food processor, finely chop the following: mushroom mixture, cream cheese, salt, parsley and basil. Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute in butter the onions, celery, garlic and mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients in bowl and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and 1/2 cup Monterey Jack cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Break up pretzels to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add melted oleo to pretzels and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
(I melt this so it's easier to spread on top of pretzels.)
After spreading the cream cheese, spread the Cool Whip on top of that.
Heat pineapple juice (almost boiling) and dissolve jello in the juice, then add the thawed strawberries.
Be sure to stir strawberries and jello regularly so they'll mix.
Put the jelled jello on top of the rest.
Keep in the refrigerator.
Yummy good!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine. Stir in flour, mustard and salt. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly (mixture should coat spoon). Remove from heat. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese, stirring until melted. Stir in cooked macaroni.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish. Top with remaining cheese. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir milk into cornmeal, sugar and salt in 2-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thick as mush; remove from heat. Stir in butter. Beat egg yolks slightly. Mix some of the hot mixture to the eggs before stirring the eggs into saucepan, mixing well. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into cornmeal mixture. Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole "floured" with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Serve hot with butter. A truly Southern dish.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare cake mix as label directs. Spoon batter into cones, filling each about 2/3 full. Place cones on large cookie sheet or jelly roll pan for easier handling. Bake cones 20 to 22
minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool cones completely on cookie sheet on wire rack.

title: texas goop
directions: Blend cream cheese, syrup and sugar.
Mix other ingredients in and chill.

title: tuna fish spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. May need to add 1 to 2 tablespoons mayonnaise. Great on crackers!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill.
Use as dip for corn chips or potato chips.
Best with cut fresh vegetables.
Makes 3 cups.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix Kool-Aid with cold water and sugar.
Stir all together and freeze.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake in a 13 x 9 pan at 350° until light brown. Mix 1/2 of Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar. Put on top of crust. Then mix chocolate pudding with 2 cups of milk and pour over cream cheese mixture. Mix vanilla pudding with 2 cups of milk and pour over chocolate mixture. Top with rest of Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: mom frey's icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, cream of tartar and add to mixture.
Dissolve soda in 1 tablespoon of cold water.
Mix thoroughly and make into 2 long rolls.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin and bake.

title: oatmeal cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat shortening, butter, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Add combined remaining ingredients; mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: craig's play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt and cream of tartar in a large saucepan. Stir in water, mixed with oil and food coloring.
Cook over medium to high heat, stirring constantly, until a ball forms. Remove from heat and knead until smooth.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar and let set overnight.
Next morning, add remaining ingredients and let set 2 to 4 hours.

title: poor man's soup or tomato italian soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add all ingredients to 2-quart pan.
Heat thoroughly and let simmer 15 minutes or awhile.
Serve with bread, biscuits, etc.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients; process in blender until smooth. Makes 1 cup.
Tastes like Eagle Brand milk.

title: spring french dressing
directions: Blend all together in blender.

title: summer tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for at least 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: ricotta cheesecake
directions: Mix cake mix by package directions.
Add lemon pudding; mix well.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix Ricotta cheese, sugar and eggs; pour over cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pear bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture.
Into the well, add oil, eggs, sugar, grated pears, nuts and vanilla. Stir only until moistened.
Grease and flour 2 (8 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Also, line bottoms with wax paper.
Spoon batter into pans dividing it evenly.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: spicy apple cider
directions: Simmer all day in slow cooker. Serve hot.

title: ham rolls
directions: Cut broccoli according to directions.
Place slice of cheese on each slice of ham.
Place broccoli on top.
Roll securely and place in shallow baking dish.
Blend soup, sour cream and mustard. Pour sauce over rolls.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: choco-dot pumpkin cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, spices and sugar.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour mixture, mixing only until combined.
Add pumpkin and vegetable oil.
Stir in cereal and chocolate morsels.
Spread evenly in an ungreased 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
Drizzle with confectioners sugar glaze, if desired.
Yield: 16 to 20 servings.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in microwave oven and pour over graham cracker crumbs.
Mix raisins, nuts and milk in thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan.
Eat.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: In saucepan, mix chicken, soup, sour cream and chilies.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon small amount of soup mix on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: "party wieners"
directions: Cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Mix the mustard and jelly into saucepan.
Add the meat.
Cover and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Serve on toothpicks or crackers.

title: spring breeze cream cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually add sugar and beat well to mix.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla until well mixed. Fold in Cool Whip until blended.
Fold in berries.	Spoon into crust and chill 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish each piece with a whole berry.
Double recipe for 9 x 13 pan.
May use frozen or fresh peaches, raspberries or blueberries.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash; drain.
Brown sausage and drain. Combine squash with all ingredients.
Add herb dressing last. (Add slowly until all ingredients are moist.)
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until puffy on top.

title: bake potato soup
directions: In a large soup kettle, melt the margarine. Heat and stir until smooth. Gradually add milk,

stirring constantly until thickened. Add potatoes and onions. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; stir until cheese is melted. Serve immediately.

title: baked chops and yams
directions: Place a layer of sliced sweet potatoes and yams on a greased casserole dish with salt and pepper and a little brown sugar. Continue layers until casserole is two-thirds full.
Heat the milk and pour it over the potatoes; it should cover them.
Place pork chops on top; cover and bake for one hour at 350°.
Remove and season with salt and pepper.
Leave cover off and cook until the chops are tender and nicely browned.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir soup and milk together.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onions and sauce; dot with butter.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: upside down pizza
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Onions are optional.
Drain.
Add mushrooms (which are optional), spaghetti sauce mix, and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Place in 9 x 13 dish.
Spread on sour cream.
Sprinkle cheese over sour cream.
Place rolls on top evenly (DO NOT ROLL UP).
Pour margarine on top.
Bake 400 degrees till golden brown.

title: hungarian squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in margarine as for pie crust.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and press into bottom and sides of 11 x 17-inch pan.
Spread fruit filling on top.
Save enough of dough to make crumb topping.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.
Good with ice cream.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked casserole cabbage
directions: Mix the eggs, milk and bread cubes.
Line baking dish with cabbage leaves.
Cut remaining cabbage in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together, except butter.
Put in cabbage-lined dish and dot with butter.
Bake until soft at 350° (40 minutes).

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Cook chicken breasts in water until tender.
Cool; peel off bone in small pieces.
Arrange broccoli in baking dish; place chicken on top.
Combine soup and mayonnaise and pour over chicken.
Put cheese on top, then sprinkle with Pepperidge Farm dressing mix (or buttered bread crumbs).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: baked beans and ground beef
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and chopped bacon.
Drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients and pour into large casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in a preheated hot 425° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chicken for a crowd
directions: Cut chicken in cubes; saute chicken in butter just until it turns white (do not brown it).
Place chicken in baking dish. Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add soup and mayo and stir until heated.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with eggs and melted butter.
Place stuffing on top of chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Additional butter is used to saute onions, celery and chicken.
Soup is mixed with milk just like normal.

title: homemade eggnog
directions: In a heavy 4-qt. saucepan, whisk together eggs, sugar and salt. Gradually add 1 qt. of milk. Cook and stir over low heat until a thermometer reads 160°-170°, about 30-35 minutes. Pour into a large heatproof bowl; stir in the vanilla, nutmeg and remaining milk. Place the bowl in an ice water bath, stirring frequently until mixture is cool. If the mixture separates, process in a blender until smooth. Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours. when ready to serve, beat the cream in a mixing bowl on high until soft peaks form. Whisk gently into the cooled milk mixture. Pour into a chilled 5 qt. punch bowl. Sprinkle with nutmeg if desired.

title: orange julius
directions: Put liquid ingredients in blender.
Add pudding mix; blend for 45 seconds.

title: temptations
directions: Cream margarine, white sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Make into ball that is small enough to fit into tea cupcake tin.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
They should be golden brown and will not look done, but they are.

title: honey-lime salad dressing
directions: Put limeade concentrate, oil, honey and salt in a blender or put in container and beat and shake thoroughly.
Add celery seed. Makes 2 cups.
Use over fresh fruit.

title: date roll candy
directions: Cook sugar, Pet milk and dates to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Add nuts, margarine, vanilla, salt and soda.
Let cool until cool enough to work with.
Sift powdered sugar on wax paper; work up candy and divide into 4 parts.
Roll into long rolls and wrap each tightly in wax paper.
Refrigerate.
Slice when ready to eat.

title: chicken bianca
directions: Place deboned chicken between 2 layers of wax paper.
Beat chicken to 1/4-inch thick.
(I use salt box or rolling pin.)
Add oil to skillet.
Heat at medium heat; add chicken.
Cook until done, but not browned.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook flour to light brown.
Add cup of water and thicken.
Add 1 cup wine; stir until thick.
Put chicken back in skillet.
Cover and simmer on low until tender, 20 minutes.
Serve with scoop of cooked, hot wild rice.

title: busy day beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat. Cut into small pieces. Heat fat in skillet. When there is about 3 tablespoons of melted fat in skillet, remove trimmings. (If fat coating is thin, add butter to make 3 tablespoons.) Quickly brown meat in fat. Add water and mushrooms (including liquid); stir in soup mix and heat to boiling. Blend sour cream and flour; add to skillet. Cook and stir until mixture thickens. Serve over hot buttered egg noodles.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand in a large mixing bowl. Put in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with ketchup and return to oven.
Bake 1 hour longer.
(Total oven time:
1 1/2 hours.)

title: sweet and saucy chicken
directions: Heat oil and brown chicken.
Remove and set aside.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Blend in flour, orange juice and chili sauce.
Add chicken.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry-raspberry jello
directions: Boil 2 cups water and mix with 1 box of jello.

Instead of cold water, add the thawed (1 package) strawberries; mix well. Add 1/2 of the chopped nuts. Let jell overnight. Pour sour cream on top of jello and refrigerate several hours. Make 2nd box of jello as before. Let partially jell, then spoon over top of sour cream.

title: sausage sauterne
directions: Simmer 2 hours. Add
2	cups oysters. Simmer 30 minutes more.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Mix all ingredients for marinade.
Marinade meat overnight. Drain marinade and bake covered at 300 degrees approximately 20 minutes per pound or until done.
Baste occasionally with marinade during baking.
Uncover, baste and brown last 20 minutes of cooking.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add sour cream.
Mix in dry ingredients. Roll 1/4 inch.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: fluffy icing
directions: Put in bowl and beat on high at least 10 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine bread crumbs and milk.
Mix with meat, onions, pepper, salt.
Shape into balls.

title: tequilaberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine salad mix, cauliflower, bacon and Parmesan. In a small bowl, combine mayo, vinegar, sugar and milk. Do not combine salad and dressing until ready to serve. Garnish with some extra bacon and Parmesan if desired. Yields about 12 servings.

title: easy oatmeal candy
directions: Boil the butter, sugar, milk and cocoa for 2 minutes (count 2 minutes from beginning of a full boil, stirring constantly). Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool. Recipe may be doubled.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain off grease. Combine mushroom soup, sour cream, water, paprika, salt and pepper; mix well. Stir in beef, carefully fold in cooked noodles. Pour into a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes, until bubbling hot.

title: grant teaff's aunt ester's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 150 cookies.

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour well.
Slice apples into a greased pie plate; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover the apples with the crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, or until apples are done.
May serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: russian borscht
directions: In a large pot, brown the meat, onions, celery, green peppers and carrots (lightly).
Add 3 quarts of water and tomatoes and bring to a boil, then simmer slowly until flavor develops and meat is tender.
Beef or chicken bouillon cubes can be added to enhance the flavor.
Peel and cut beets; slice cabbage and add to soup.
Cook until vegetables are done.

title: hillshire farm sausage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon dressing for tossed salad
directions: Cook eggs, vinegar, sugar and water until thickened.
Crumble bacon over dressing and stir together.
Serve over crisp bed of lettuce.

title: pork roast tenderloin
directions: Salt and pepper loin and sprinkle garlic powder over and refrigerate overnight.
Mix together celery, apple and onion.
Put this mixture on a large piece of foil and place the pork loin on top and wrap tightly.
Cook in a roasting pan at 350° until tender.
Slice kiwi fruit and serve with stuffed prunes.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine brown sugar and water.
Cook over low heat until it reaches the bubble stage.
Add pecans and butter.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Put broth in the pot.
Add vegetables.
Stir for a couple of minutes.
Put in oven at 320° for 30 minutes.
"This stew is very good also with French bread."

title: calico beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In Dutch oven brown ground beef with bacon pieces and onion; drain.
Add large can of baked beans, undrained, and drained lima and kidney beans.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Or microwave at medium temperature for 20 minutes.)

title: unbaked chocolate bars
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chips; cool slightly.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: depression cake
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, raisins, hot water, oil, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil.
Continue cooking on a low boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: orange bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine cereal and buttermilk; let stand 5 minutes until cereal is softened.
Add oil, orange peel and egg whites; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Batter can be baked immediately or stored in a tightly covered container in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: nutty brownies
directions: Butter a 9-inch square pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine and sugar; beat.
Add vanilla, salt and eggs, then beat. Add cocoa, baking powder and flour.
Stir in nuts.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: In a wide mouthed clear salad bowl, spread lettuce leaves evenly.
Layer with celery, onions, cooked peas and water chestnuts.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over top of salad.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp au gratin
directions: Melt
oleo.
Add
flour, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, milk and cheese.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.
Add shrimp; heat until shrimp is heated, about 4 to 5 minutes.

title: chew bread
directions: Melt margarine.
Cream with sugar and eggs. Add flour and vanilla.
Pour in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.
Chocolate chips and nuts may be omitted, if desired.

title: hamburger baked beans
directions: Brown meat and chopped onions; drain well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey turnovers(serves 4)
directions: Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
On a lightly floured surface, roll each rectangle of dough to approximately 7 x 8-inch. Mix all other ingredients in a bowl.
Spoon 1/4 of the mixture diagonally onto half of each piece of dough, leaving a 1/4-inch border.
Lightly brush edges of dough with water, then fold dough over, forming triangles.
Press edges together to seal.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Wash chicken in cold water and drain.
Roll chicken pieces in mixture of flour, salt and pepper, covering well.
Brown in shortening.
Place in baking dish.
Pour milk over chicken.
Add the water and bay leaf and sprinkle generously with paprika. Cover and bake.
Remove cover during last 15 minutes or longer to finish browning.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed, but use milk in place of water.
Pour cake mix over nuts and coconut.
Melt cream cheese and butter, then add powdered sugar and spoon over top of cake batter.
Don't spread.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: grouper cheeks stew(my own original)
directions: Prepare fish:
Soak in ice water; feel for a small angular bone.
Peel off any skin.
Cut into pieces (1-inch size).
Peel and cube potato.
Chop onion and celery.
Saute vegetables in 2 tablespoons oil about 8 minutes (do not overcook potato).
Dissolve chicken cube in 1 cup boiling water.
Add to vegetables.
Liquid should "cover" vegetables.
Cook about 6 minutes.
Lay fish over potato.
Do not stir or break up fish.
Simmer about 6 minutes, just enough to cook fish.
Break up bay leaf, lay on fish.
Scald milk.
Add to pot.
Season with pepper, dry parsley and dill weed. Crush 5 crackers.
Add to thicken.
Serves 4. So good!

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar, then Cool Whip.
Add the rest of the fruit.
Put in container that can be put in freezer.

title: indian corn bread pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion well in a skillet. Mix in the remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes. Turn into a greased casserole. Mix corn bread as directed on package and spread on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Combine salmon, soup, cheese and rice.
Saute onion and celery in butter; add to salmon mixture.
Pour into casserole dish; top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Beat eggs. Sift flour and cream of tartar together. Gradually mix flour with the eggs and blend well.
Add the flour and eggs to the creamed shortening and sugar.
Mix well. Chill dough.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk.
Add flour and vanilla; mix well.
Chill dough.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Place on greased sheet.
Gently press M&M's or pecan halves into each cookie.
Bake at 325° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy pancakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Slowly add milk and beat with a whisk until pours very easily.
Pour onto heated nonstick pan or griddle (about 400°) to desired size of pancake.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef fine.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients, reserving some chopped dried beef to cover outside of ball.
Shape in a ball and roll in reserved beef.
Refrigerate and serve with crackers.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Mix in order and fill shells.
Chill well.

title: easy fudge frosting
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes and then stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Beat in remaining ingredients until well blended and smooth.
If frosting becomes too thick, beat in additional milk until of spreading consistency.
Makes 2 1/2 cups or enough to frost top and sides of two (9-inch) round cake layers.

title: aunt martha's round steak
directions: Mix 1/2 can water into the can of soup.
Put in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Cut steak into strips (2 x 3-inches).
Salt and pepper steak.
Put into mushrooms soup and sprinkle top with dry onion soup.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve on buttered noodles.

title: two-potato bake
directions: Coat an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Layer 2 cups sweet potatoes in half of dish; layer 2 cups red potatoes in other half.
Sprinkle with onion.
Drizzle with half of margarine.
Sprinkle with half of salt and pepper.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bring milk to a boil; pour over.
Cover with foil.
Cut 8 slits in foil.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with parsley and cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Mix and melt 2 minutes.
Then boil 2 minutes.
Line greased cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Cover with chopped pecans. Cover with sugar mix and bake at 350° for 16 minutes.
Cool and break apart and store in airtight container.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat eggs and set aside.
Mix baking powder with flour.
Cream sugar, butter and shortening with eggs.
Add flour mixture and sweet milk (a little at a time).
Add flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Put in cold oven and turn heat to 350°; bake for 1 hour or until done.
Test:
Stick in a toothpick; when it comes out clean, it's done.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix hamburger, taco mix and beans and place in 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with sour cream, taco sauce and Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let stand 1 hour.
Sift together flour, soda and spices.
Beat eggs and add oil and vanilla.
Add apple mixture; combine flour mix with eggs.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and top with corn flakes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: courtney's carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil. Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add to egg mixture. Blend well and add grated carrots. Bake in 9 x 9 pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Cook the raisins in water; set aside.
Add brown sugar, mustard and cornstarch and slowly stir in the vinegar, lemon rind and lemon juice.
In 1 1/2 cups of water, cook until thick, then add raisins and butter.
Cook over low heat.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and coloring; beat 10 minutes.
Add buttermilk and slowly add the flour.
Add salt, vanilla and cocoa.
Remove bowl from mixer and add by hand, mixing lightly, the vinegar and soda.
Grease and flour pan before adding mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Place cake side up.
Prick cake with utility fork.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Pour carefully over cake.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Dip cake pan in warm water for 10 seconds. Turn out onto serving plate.
Top with Cool Whip and sides, too.

title: summertime tea
directions: Steep tea bags and 4 cups boiling water 5 minutes.
Add the rest of ingredients.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chips and cheese.
Spread in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese and top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal and raisin and cinnamon cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand 1 hour.
Cream together shortening, brown sugar and sugar.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon into sugar mixture and mix well.
Blend in eggs and raisins.
Add oatmeal (very stiff dough).

title: chicken salad balls(appetizer)
directions: Mix all above ingredients.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Melt butter
in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread other ingredients in layers.
Pour milk evenly over top.	Bake at 325° until brown.

title: irish cream liquor
directions: Put the first five ingredients in blender; blend about 45 seconds.
Add 1 cup whiskey and blend only long enough to mix, about 10 seconds.
Best if chilled overnight.
Mix before serving. Makes about 1 quart.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together 2 c. sugar,
eggs
and 1 cup oil.
Add the remaining ingredients, mix	and
put
into	a
greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party pizzas
directions: Grind together the 3 ingredients.
Mix with mayonnaise to make it the consistency of tuna fish.
Spread on party rye and broil until bubbly.

title: eggless and sugarless carrot cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients into saucepan. Mix well. Bring to a boil slowly, stirring constantly. Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat; cool. Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt in bowl. Add to carrot mixture, mixing well. Fold in pecans. Spoon into well-greased and floured 9-inch ring mold. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Form into 1-inch balls. Chill.
Fry meatballs in oil.
Make gravy as directions say, using 1 1/4 cups water.
Add 1/2 cup real mayonnaise.
Pour over meatballs.
Makes about 45 meatballs.

title: low-fat chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch chunks.
Combine corn flake crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into butter; roll in crumb mixture and arrange chicken in single layer on foil-lined baking dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: rag doll salad
directions: Place 1 peach half for body on salad plate.
Arrange 4 small celery sticks for arms and legs around peach half.
Use 1 large marshmallow for head, raisins for eyes, nose, shoe and buttons and small piece maraschino cherry for mouth.
Spread yellow cheese; arrange around marshmallow for hair.
Add a skirt of leaf lettuce to complete the salad.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can onion rings.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole. Bake covered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in 10-inch tube pan.

title: old fashioned boiled custard
directions: Put milk in top of double boiler.
Stir in eggs and sugar. Stir well.
Cook until it begins to get thick (do not boil).
Stir constantly.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Combine peanuts, red food color, sugar and water in saucepan. Cook over medium heat until water evaporates.
Place peanuts on cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, stirring often to prevent burning.

title: chicken a la king with rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in a large skillet until lightly browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chilled avocado soup
directions: Puree the avocados in blender.
Add consomme, sour cream, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate until chilled. Garnish each serving with a slice of lime and a teaspoon of sour cream.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add the beaten eggs to milk and oatmeal.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on buttered pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add broccoli, soup and water.
Cover.
Simmer until onion, celery and broccoli are tender. Put rice in bottom of dish.
Pour broccoli mixture over rice.
Top with Cheez Whiz.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: almost fat-free cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sour cream and beat until smooth, then add Cool Whip and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and sugar and mix.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: health watcher garden pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into jelly roll pan; bake at 375° for 8 minutes, then cool.
Mix yogurt, salad dressing, Ricotta and dressing mix.
Spread mixture on cooled crust.
Top with slices of favorite veggies and season with Mrs. Dash.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Sprinkle evenly with grated cheese and garnish with olives.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush
cookies
in blender.
Place all ingredients into nice flowerpot
in
this
order:
cookies
in pot; margarine, whipped topping,
xxx sugar and cream cheese mixed;
cookies; pudding, milk and vanilla (mixed until thick); thick layers of cookies
on top; decorated with candy worms and plastic flowers.
Serve with plastic shovel.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight and drain off water.
Fill Dutch oven 1/2 full with water.
Add ham bone, beans, onions, celery and seasonings.
Simmer for at least 4 hours. Remove ham bone. Cut up ham and return to soup. Continue to simmer.
After it has thickened, add tomato soup and water to desired consistency.

title: superb cherry dessert
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Spread into ungreased 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: italian chicken wings
directions: Remove wing tips before washing chicken well.
In a large bowl, combine chicken and dressing. Toss a bit.
Cover and marinate about 1 hour in refrigerator. Toss once or twice during the hour.
In a medium bowl, combine bread crumbs and garlic powder. Stir. Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake marinade off gently so it's not dripping. Coat each piece well in bread crumbs.
Place on
nonstick or sprayed cookie sheets. Bake about 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: mama's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into balls. Flatten with a fork. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Begin by crossing the 2 slices of bacon and place the tenderloin where the bacon slices cross.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stack the onion, tomato and green pepper on meat.
Bring the bacon slices up around the stack and secure them on top with several toothpicks.
Grill for 45 minutes.
Can place cheese on top 10 to 15 minutes before package is done (optional).
Each package serves 1 person.

title: paul reeve's chicken paprika
directions: Dice celery, green pepper, onions, tomatoes, carrot and garlic; set aside.
Season chicken pieces with salt and pepper to taste. Heat oil over medium-high heat in a large saucepan.
Brown chicken pieces until golden brown.
Add diced vegetables and half the paprika.
Cover; reduce heat to low.
Allow chicken to simmer in juices that cook out from the vegetables for approximately 20 minutes.
Check the pot.
Add the remaining paprika.
Simmer for another 15 to 20 minutes, or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread in large bowl.
Add pepper, corn, celery and onions.
Add mayonnaise and stir until moistened.
Fold in chopped tomatoes.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: fresh lemonade syrup base(my grandmother's)
directions: Dissolve sugar in
boiling water.
Add lemon peel and juice. Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Makes 2 2/3 cups base.

title: cranberry christmas punch
directions: Chill.	Just before serving add 2 quarts ginger ale.
May serve with orange rings, ice ring with strawberries frozen in it, etc.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oats.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Allow to cool for at least 1 hour.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package.
Mix soups, sour cream and chicken.
Top with stuffing in baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice cheese bake
directions: Saute celery, carrot and onion in butter.
Combine with rice, parsley, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix together chicken soup, broth, mayonnaise and milk.
Lay chicken slices on top of rice mixture.
Pour chicken soup mix on top.
Lay cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for an hour, covered.

title: orange coconut chews
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar. Blend in egg, vanilla and orange rind. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Add to first mixture and blend well. Add dates and coconut. Bake in a 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into squares when cool.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Mix in large skillet (2 1/2-quart).
Brown ground chuck in melted margarine.
Add beans, soup mix and other ingredients. Pour into bean pot.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Measure oatmeal, flour, sugar, brown sugar, raisins, soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in oil, egg and vanilla.
Mixture may seem almost dry.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage until done, drain.
Place cheese, milk, pimento, and sausage in a crock pot.
Cover.
Cook until cheese melts. Turn down on low.
Keep warm.

title: never fail popcorn balls
directions: Boil syrup, sugar and vinegar to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and soda.
Stir until foamy.
Then pour over 5 to 6 quarts popped corn.
Stir gently until cool enough to form into balls.
Dip hands into cold water to keep from sticking.

title: taco pizza
directions: Mix together and spread on foil covered pizza pan.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, black olives and 2 cups sharp Cheddar cheese. Serve with Doritos.

title: chicken salad on cantaloupe rings
directions: In a large bowl combine chicken, celery, grapes and parsley. Combine the next seven ingredients; mix well.
Pour over chicken mixture and toss.
Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: old fashioned lemon icebox pie
directions: Chill milk in freezer for 45 minutes to one hour.
Cover bottom of loaf pan with crushed cookie crumbs.
Whip chilled milk until it stands in peaks (will look like whipped cream).
Now slowly add sugar while beating with mixer.
Add eggs, beating well after each one.
Add strained lemon juice and the grated lemon rind.
Pour into the crust lined loaf pan and freeze for several hours.
This is a wonderful light, refreshing dessert.
Mash and sweeten strawberries to serve on top of each slice.

title: chunky chicken chili(serves 6; good use for leftover cooked chicken)
directions: Coat Dutch oven with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion, green pepper, jalapeno and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add chili powder and cumin; cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken, 1 cup water, cayenne, black pepper, Worcestershire sauce, Dijon mustard, stewed tomatoes, chicken broth and chili sauce; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add beans and cook 5 minutes.

title: louisiana pie
directions: In medium size bowl, combine butter, sugar and salt; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla, flour, cream and pecans.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Serve slightly warm with whipped cream.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine beef, beans, oregano, cumin and garlic powder.
Place 4 of uncooked noodles in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Spread on 1/2 of beef mixture and cover with remaining noodles. Combine water and salsa.
Pour over all.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until noodles are tender.
Combine sour cream, onions and olives, then spoon over dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered until cheese melts.

title: spinach brownies
directions: Sift flour.
Add eggs, milk and butter to flour mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and stir.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cold, cut into squares.
May be frozen.
Reheat at 325°.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Store in airtight container until ready to use.
Place 1/4 cup mixture in serving cup and fill with boiling water.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake until well mixed.
Set aside.
Tear spinach into bite sized pieces and place in a large salad bowl.
Pour dressing over spinach and toss lightly.
Garnish with bacon and egg.

title: ham spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve on crackers.

title: sausage mozzarella supper
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Mix with the spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, tomato juice, onions, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Grease eight 6-quart baking pans.
Layer half of noodles, sliced cheese and meat sauce in pans.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle shredded cheese equally over each pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Yields 150 to 175 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix together and beat with hand mixer until blended all ingredients.
Pour ingredients into a 9-inch lightly greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rumaki
directions: You will also need 2 boxes of round toothpicks.

title: goop
directions: Mix cornstarch and water.
Add optional color.
Pour in tray or tub.
Experience and enjoy this unique mixture's properties.
Feels really different.

title: sandwich omelet
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Place slices of bread in pan buttered side down.
Place slice of ham and cheese on each bread slice.
Top with slice of bread, buttered side up.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour melted butter and corn flakes over top of egg mixture.
Bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.

title: english trifle
directions: Cut sponge fingers in half and lay in bottom of large glass dish.
Cover with the raspberries.

title: hot dip-zippy spread
directions: Mix and spoon into 8-inch pie plate; sprinkle with pecans or walnuts; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon, then add oil and eggs one at a time.
Add carrots; blend well.
Pour batter into lightly floured pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: no cook pickles
directions: Mix brine; do not cook.
Pour over cukes and onions.
Keep unsealed in refrigerator.
It will keep 4 months in refrigerator. Makes 1 gallon.

title: spanish onions
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Pour soup into bacon and fat and stir. Oil dish and pour a little of the ingredients in the bottom, then place onions in dish. Put remaining sauce on onion mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Brush with margarine before you break into crumbs.
Put in a dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes, meat and salad.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole bowl, stir together the peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook for 8 minutes in microwave on High, stirring well after 4 minutes.
After 8 minutes, stir in butter and vanilla.
Microwave 2 minutes longer on High.
Remove from microwave.
Add baking soda; quickly stir until light and foamy. Pour immediately onto lightly greased cookie sheet, spread thin.

title: chicken and sour cream enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together 1 cup sour cream, 1 cup cheese, chicken, 1/4 cup salsa, cilantro and cumin. Spoon 1/4 cup chicken mixture on each tortilla. Place seam side down in baking dish (13 x 9). Top with remaining 3/4 of salsa. Cover. Bake for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Continue to bake until cheese melts. Top with lettuce and chopped tomato. Serve with remaining sour cream.

title: b~b~q sauce
directions: Mix all and add garlic salt and black pepper to taste.
Boil until slightly thick, stirring occasionally.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dough will be very stiff (may have to use hands).
Divide dough in half and press in 9-inch ungreased cake pans. Cut in wedges and prick with fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut again before removing from pan.
Cool slightly before removing from pan with spatula.

title: blooming onion
directions: Whisk until smooth; let rest 45 minutes.

title: greek hummus dip
directions: Drain beans, reserving liquid from cans.
Put beans and other ingredients in a blender or food processor and whirl until smooth, adding enough reserved bean liquid to give the mixture a creamy consistency.
Serve as a dip with pita bread cut into pie-shaped wedges and baked at 350° for 7 minutes, or until slightly crisp. Makes 3 cups.

title: prize coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Beat well. Alternately add flour and milk.
Stir in coconut and vanilla. Pour in two 9-inch pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cake is cool, frost with 7-Minute Frosting.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Saute onions and add to ground chuck.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Makes 18 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan or iron skillet. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to directions on box.
Drain. Mix with Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Mix in rice.
Bake until bubbly.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together, except cheese.
Grease skillet.
Sprinkle with flour.
Pour in half of the
mixture.
Top with the cheese. Pour remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: jamesville strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add hot water.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Cool thoroughly.
Add sliced berries and spoon into the pie shells. Chill.
Top with whipped topping as directed.

title: fiesta liver
directions: Saute small cubes of liver that have been floured on each side. Remove from oil.
Saute onion and green pepper in remaining oil. Add liver and remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. Good served over rice.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Peel rhubarb and cut into 1/2-inch slices before measuring. Wash and cut strawberries in pieces.
Line a pie pan with plain pastry.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and eggs.
Add to the rhubarb and strawberries and turn into pan.
Moisten edge of crust with water. Cover with a top crust or cover with crumbs.
If covering with crust, press edges together, then trim.
Gash top to let steam escape.
Bake in quick oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and continue baking at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Place 18 frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle pudding over rolls.
Melt in a small saucepan margarine and brown sugar, heat until hot.
Pour over rolls.
Let rise 10 to 12 hours or overnight.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 15 minutes then turn out on plate.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: sausage stew
directions: Cut sausage in 1/2-inch slices.
Fry until browned.
Add soup and water, if needed.
Add vegetables.
If necessary, parboil the vegetables before adding to the stew.

title: guilt-free pina colada
directions: In blender, combine the yogurts, pineapple juice concentrate, coconut and rum extracts; add a few cubes of ice and pulse several times until ice is coarsely chopped.
Continue adding ice, pulsing after each addition, until mixture is smooth and creamy.
(If thicker colada is desired, add more ice.)
Pour into two 12 oz. glasses and garnish each with lime slice.

title: country 10 bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Mix beans and water; add next 4 ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with corn bread.

title: macaroni sausage casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water 7 to 8 minutes.
Drain Well.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice.
Place in saucepan.
Add milk and sugar; stir. Bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to medium. Simmer until thick and creamy, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour into medium bowl.
Stir in vanilla; cool.
Fold in topping and fruit just before serving.
Serves 4.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost and squeeze out all the water from the spinach.
Puree the water chestnuts.
Mix all together and let set for 4 to 6 hours in refrigerator.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Put in can of cream of celery or mushroom soup.
Add sweet milk.
Stir in uncooked rice.
Place on top of the mixture several browned pork chops.
Add a few slices of onion and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a covered casserole dish.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening and mix well.
Add milk and mix.
Divide dough in half and roll out to fit a 9 x 13-inch or an 11 x 15-inch pan.
Place dough in bottom and fill with apple slices.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Roll other half and cover top of apples.
Make slits with knife.

title: cheese wafers
directions: In a bowl, combine cheese, flour and cayenne pepper. Pour melted butter over mixture and blend well with hands. Pinch off walnut-sized pieces of dough and roll in hands to form small balls. Place dough on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 18 minutes (dough will flatten as it bakes). Makes about 40.

title: eggs for brunch(servings:  8)
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Butter pan.
Mix eggs, milk and Tabasco.
Put eggs in bottom of pan, then add bread and grated cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Serving Ideas:
For a twist, add sausage.

title: silver dollar pickles
directions: Dissolve lime in water; soak cucumbers in mixture 24 hours. Drain; cover with clean water and soak another 3 hours.
Drain. Place spices in cheesecloth.
Mix vinegar, salt and sugar for syrup.
Let cucumbers stand in syrup 2 hours.
Bring to boil; simmer 35 minutes.
Seal hot.

title: chocolate almond shake(serves 1)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium-high speed until smooth.
Pour into chilled glass.

title: orange vegetable pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
In a large Dutch oven, heat cooking oil.
Brown meat in the hot oil.
Spoon off fat.
Add orange peel, orange juice, onions, fines herbes and bay leaf. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: myrt's baked eggplant
directions: Peel
and dice eggplant and cook until tender in enough salted water
to	cover (about 15 minutes).
Drain off water. Stir
in diced green pepper and diced onion.
Add most of the cracker crumbs
and
beaten egg.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Dot with
butter
and sprinkle on remainder of cracker crumbs. Moisten top with milk.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until firm.
Very good.

title: pineapple nut pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice slowly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Use graham cracker crust.
Makes 3 eight-inch pies or 2 nine-inch pies.

title: pork with sweet peppers
directions: Mix together the flour, thyme and black pepper.
Remove bones and excess fat from chops.
Dredge in flour mixture.
Spray frying pan and heat until hot.
Brown pork and remove to a warm platter. Drain excess fat from pan.
Add peppers, scallions and garlic. Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Combine beef stock, cornstarch and rosemary. Add to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook just until thick.
Pour over pork.

title: beef ball
directions: Wash off beef slices in cold water. Pat dry with paper towel. Put in blender. Blend together with remaining ingredients. Chill and shape. Roll in beef.

title: talorone
directions: Fry meat, onions and peppers until almost done.
Add corn, chili powder, tomato sauce and soup.
While hot, add cheese and salt.
Prepare noodles and mix all together.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle more cheese on top.
Bake at 300 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar in large bowl; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas.
Stir enough to combine; do not beat.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chess squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine, 1 egg and cake mix. Mix thoroughly and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In medium saucepan stir sugar, water, salt and cornstarch. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook and stir for 1 minute (until thick and glossy).
Remove from heat and stir in jello.
Let cool to medium temperature.
Place half berries in pie shell.
Place 1/2 filling over berries.
Add remaining berries to pie and cover with remaining filling.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: breakfast surprise
directions: Cook the sausage, drain and crumble up.
Put 1/2 of the cheese in the bottom of crust.
Mix in a bowl the eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Add remainder of the cheese and add the crumbled up sausage.
Pour into the pie crust and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Step 1:
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add brown sugar, can of drained crushed pineapple and can of drained chunk pineapple. Warm completely, but do not boil.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Flour and grease 3 medium loaf pans or 6 mini loaf pans.
In a large mixing bowl combine oil and sugar.
Mix well on high speed.
Add eggs.
Mix in pumpkin and water; use hands or low speed.
Stir in nuts.
Divide mixture evenly.
Bake 60 or 70 minutes, until pick comes out clean.
Let cool in pans about 10 minutes.
Then turn out on racks.
Serve warm or freeze for later.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix and shape into balls.
Mix 1/2 cup catsup and 1/2 cup water together; pour over meatballs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes and then turn oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: flemish rice-milk
directions: Put a pan on the fire with the milk and pinch of salt.
Add the rice and cinnamon. Cook while stirring.

On a low fire, let the rice-milk simmer for about 45 minutes, regularly stirring the mass. Away from the fire, add the sugar and the saffron. Spread over plates and eat it warm or cold with plenty of brown or candy sugar on top.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Grate cheese; add sausage, Bisquick and finely grated or chopped green chilies.
Shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: picnic chicken
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4 inch thickness.
In a shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken in egg, then in the crumb mixture.
In a skillet, brown the chicken in oil and butter over medium heat for 3-5 minutes on each side or until juices run clear.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: portabellas topped with potatoes and brie
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Scrub the potatoes and prick them with a fork, then bake until soft, about 45 to 60 minutes.
While the potatoes are baking, clean the mushrooms. Remove stems, trim their bases and set aside.
Using a melon baller, scoop out the thick part of the mushrooms so you have a shell about 1/4-inch thick. Combine scraped-out bits with the stems and chop coarsely.

title: fruit juice surprise
directions: Cut up fruit and place some in each glass. Add juice.

title: spiced peach dessert
directions: Drain peaches, reserving juice.
Set peaches aside.
Combine cornstarch and spices in a medium saucepan.
Stir in peach juice and rind.
Add peaches to mixture in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and serve warm.

title: finger paints
directions: Mix starch with enough cold water to make a paste.
Add boiling water and cook over low heat until glossy.
Remove from heat and add soap flakes.
When cool, add glycerin.
Stir in food coloring.
Use on freezer paper.

title: new wine
directions: Mix together.
Chill or serve over ice.
Refreshing.
Good and full of minerals and vitamins.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all together and marinate in refrigerator for at least 24 hours before serving. Keeps well in fridge.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill before serving (better if you refrigerate overnight).

title: "frannie bell's" coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, flour, baking powder and salt.
Then add milk and coconut flavoring. Beat well. Fold in coconut. Bake in a tube or Bundt pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: summer fry
directions: Chop all vegetables and mix in a large bowl until all are moist (you may need to add
2 or 3 tablespoons water).
Put corn meal and flour into a large paper grocery bag.
Add vegetables (1/3 at a time) and shake until coated.
Fry in hot peanut oil until crisp.
(Deep fryer works well.) Drain well.
Summer squash is good in this too.
Not for the fat conscious, but very good!

title: white bread
directions: Place the yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water; stir until well blended.
Pour one cup of boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt; mix together.
Add one cup cold milk.
Add yeast to the milk mixture.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Bring mixture to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove spices and serve.

title: smoky clam cheese log
directions: Drain clams.
Shape 1 package cream cheese long and flat, 15 x 12-inches.
Place on large sheet of waxed paper.
Top with drained clams.
Shape remaining cream cheese, 12 x 2-inches; place over clams.
Tuck in ends.
Roll and press to seal seams, using waxed paper to ease rolling.
Roll in parsley and nuts.
Chill.
Spread over bread.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sausage and potatoes au gratin
directions: Make patties out of sausage; cook and drain and break into small pieces.
Combine soup, milk, onion, green pepper, pimento, salt and pepper; blend well.
Place half potatoes in a greased (2-quart) casserole.
Add half the sausage.
Cover with half the soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 1/4 hours.
Remove cover; sprinkle with cheese and bake, uncovered, another 15 minutes or more or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil cans of milk for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Important:
Watch water level; do not let all the water evaporate.
If water evaporates, cans will explode.
Let cans cool in water for about 2 hours.
Spoon caramel into graham cracker crust; chill.
Top with Cool Whip and chocolate chip drops (or any other topping).

title: calico vegetables
directions: Drain corn and beans.
Mix with green pepper, onion and celery in bowl.
Add cheese and sour cream; mix well.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Toss cracker crumbs with margarine in a bowl.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. Yields 6 servings.

title: wagon wheel dip
directions: Mix well in blender.
Makes 3 cups.

title: mushroom pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from roast.
Coat meat with flour.
In Dutch oven, brown meat on both sides in hot shortening.
Season with salt and pepper; add onions.
Combine water, catsup, sherry, garlic, mustard, marjoram and bay leaf; add to meat.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours or until tender.
Remove meat to platter. Discard bay leaf.
Skim excess fat from pan juices.
Add mushrooms to pan juices.
Blend cold water with 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour; stir into juices.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Drizzle a little gravy over roast; pass remaining gravy. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into pieces.
Cook until tender.
Drain and chill.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: candied carrots
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add carrots.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nutmeg.
Simmer, covered for 10 minutes.
Cook uncovered for 5 minutes.
Longer or until carrots are glazed, stirring frequently.

title: feather rolls
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let dough rise 2 to 4 hours.
Divide dough in half, roll each half in a round circle, about 1/3-inch thick.
Butter the dough and cut like pie wedges.
Roll from big end to make the point on top.
Let rise on greased pans, until light, up to 3 hours.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
These will be light as a feather.

title: english muffins in a loaf
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat milk and water to 120° to 130°.
Add to dry mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in additional flour to make stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches).
(Pans are greased and sprinkled with corn meal.)
Sprinkle tops with corn meal.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes to 1 hour in warm place.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Immediately remove from pans and cool.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
Mix egg and vinegar together; beat for 1 minute.
Add water and mix well.
Pour liquid into crumb mixture.
Mix well.
Divide into balls.
Roll crust out on floured surface.
Put in pie pan and bake until done.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan; stir in flour and salt. Add milk, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens. Add potatoes and heat, stirring, until it boils again.
Turn potatoes into a shallow greased casserole.
Spread 1 tablespoon melted butter over top.
Place on a rack above the middle of the oven and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Heat caramels and 1/4 cup of the milk over medium, stirring until smooth; set aside.
Mix cake mix, butter, nuts and remaining milk; spread 1/2 of this mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake only 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle on chocolate chips, then pour on caramel and cover with rest of cake mix.

(Sometimes it's too thick to pour, so I pat the dough out into little tortilla shapes and put them over the top.) Bake about 15 minutes longer until cake part is slightly dry to the touch. Cool completely, cut and eat!!
Serves 2.

title: reception punch
directions: Combine water and sugar; stir until sugar is dissolved. Add frozen juice concentrates. Stir until concentrates are well combined. Add pineapple juice and lime juice. Chill thoroughly.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over batter.
Pour melted margarine over mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (until knife comes out clean).
Keep refrigerated.

title: trash
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients. Place in a large grocery sack with 1 pound powdered sugar. Shake well to coat.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually along with vanilla
and
salt.
Mix in the chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls
on
a
greased cookie tin.
Put cookies in preheated oven
and turn the oven off.
Leave in overnight.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Saute chopped onion and minced garlic lightly in olive oil. Combine Ricotta cheese, grated Romano or Parmesan, raw spinach (which has been washed carefully, drained and chopped coarsely), sauteed onion and garlic, beaten eggs, salt, pepper and parsley. Mix well.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake as directed on package.

title: baked beans
directions: Top with bacon.
Bake for 1 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cut butter and Crisco into dry ingredients as for pie dough.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening and add sugar.
Beat well and add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon juice and lemon extract.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with milk, beating well.
Bake in regular tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Use regular size tube pan.
Don't preheat oven and don't peek!

title: 7-up salad
directions: Heat 7-Up.
Pour over gelatin; mix cream cheese with hot water until smooth.
Add cheese and remaining ingredients together. Chill.

title: seven seas casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, water, salt, onion and pepper. Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour half of mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Make 3 layers in casserole, using Minute rice and tuna, peas, onions and soup.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cooking dish.
Cover with cheese slices and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage with onion and bell pepper.
Drain well.
Add sauce, chilies and cheese (cubed), stirring until cheese melts.
Serve while hot with your favorite chips.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add soup and 1 can of broth from chicken.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in oleo; add soup mixture.
Cook spaghetti until tender; drain.
Add to soup mixture and jalapeno Cheez Whiz and pimientos.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pepper nuts
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until well blended.
Mix dry ingredients until firm dough is achieved.
Refrigerate until cold. Cut into shapes or slice.
Bake at 350° until brown or firm, approximately 5 to 7 minutes.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole stir together sugar, syrup. Microwave on high 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts;
cook 3-5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Cook 1-2 minutes.
Peanuts well be brown; add soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour on lightly buttered cookie sheet.

title: energy bars
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in a microwave oven on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
(Optional:
Toast Rice Krispies and Minute Oats in oven at 300° for 10 minutes.)
Mix Rice Krispies and Minute Oats into the marshmallow mixture.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Pat mixture evenly, using plastic wrap.
Cool.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix well the peanut butter and Karo syrup.
Add the Rice Krispies; mix until the Rice Krispies are well coated.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Press 1/2 gallon of ice cream on top.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Freeze.

title: yogurt cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Fold in pineapple.
Chill until serving time.
Spoon into 4 sherbet glasses.
Garnish with chopped pecans.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ice cream
directions: Use very fresh eggs (they should sink when put in a bowl of cold water).

title: sugar-free sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, 3/4 of brown sugar substitute, milk, egg, melted margarine and vanilla.
Stir until well blended. Spoon into shallow baking dish coated with cooking spray.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients except carrots and cook 5 minutes on medium heat. Pour over carrots and heat.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Stir together meat, salsa, corn, mayonnaise and chili powder. Layer 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 chips; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with fresh tomatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, syrup and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 unbaked pastry shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: perogie casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
In skillet, melt 1 stick of margarine and cook onions until tender.
Cook potatoes and mash (do not add milk). Add 1/2 stick margarine, cheese and half of the onions to potatoes and beat until cheese is melted.
Layer potatoes and noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Very good.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim brown edges of bread.
Butter both sides and place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage, drain and sprinkle over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs and half and half and pour over cheese.
Cover and leave in the refrigerator overnight.

title: sausage bread
directions: Defrost bread according to package directions.
Roll out to rectangle or circle.
Place filling in middle; roll up jelly roll fashion.
Seal the ends.
Put sealed end on a greased cookie tray. Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Make sure to prick top of dough.
Provolone or Mozzarella can also be added to filling.

title: busy day brownies
directions: Combine in a large bowl all ingredients and beat with hand mixer just until blended.
Spread mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: minivera's torte
directions: Mix sugar, egg yolks, cornstarch and hot milk and cook over low heat until thick.
Cool; add vanilla.
Crush 1 box zwieback; add 2 tablespoons sugar and melted margarine.
Press mixture firmly in 8-inch pie plate, reserving some crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Make topping with 3 egg whites, beaten stiff.
Brown in hot oven.

title: hearty tuna casserole
directions: Drain and flake tuna fish.
Cook noodles.
Combine noodles with tuna, peas, celery and green onions.
Blend sour cream, mustard, mayonnaise, vegetable dip and a dash of Tabasco, if desired.
Mix all together in a casserole dish and top with bread crumbs, cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: passion pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix just until blended.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.

title: pastry - butter dips
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl; add milk.
Stir until stiff; roll out on floured board or press out with fingers.
Cut in 1/4-inch strips. Dip strips in butter.
Place in same pan.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
18 strips.

title: green beans-hominy bake
directions: Drain the hominy, reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Chop half of the French-fried
onions.
Combine
hominy,
reserved liquid, chopped onion,
green
beans,
soup, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Put into
1/2-quart casserole and bake, covered, at 375° for 25 to 30	minutes.
Uncover
and	top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Note:
Raisins should be put in a bowl and covered with hot water and let stand while mixing cookies.

title: good and easy salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pudding in saucepan; add water and bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Chill until thick.
Mix in nutmeg and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into mold and set for at least 3 hours.

title: grapefruit, pineapple salad
directions: Cut grapefruits crosswise; scoop out fruit with spoon.
Save the juice.
With sharp knife and clean hands, carefully remove membranes and lining from grapefruit hulls.
Set aside.

title: western bean casserole
directions: Place cooked meat, onion soup mix, water, catsup, mustard, vinegar and beans in a 2-quart baking dish.
Mix well.
Bake in 400° oven for about 30 minutes or until bean mixture is bubbly hot. Top with bacon.
Makes 10 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, butter, vanilla, cocoa and salt. Add flour; mix well. Add coconut and pecans. Bake in greased pan for 25-30 minutes at 350 degrees. Don't over bake. As soon as you take out of oven spread marshmallow cream over top.

title: raisin cake
directions: Place first 4 items in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Cool.

title: black forest cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Press onto bottom and sides of pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, granulated sugar and vanilla at medium speed of electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in chocolate and cream.
Pour into crust.
Bake 1 hour or until center is almost set.
Cool completely, remove rim.
Chill.
Spread pie filling over the top. Serve with whipped cream around edges, cherry filling in middle, chocolate peeled and laid on whipped cream.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Drain juice off of pineapple.
Heat; add jello and let cool. Whip Dream Whip.
Add Dream Whip, cottage cheese and chopped pecans to jello mixture.
chill.
This looks real pretty in a Tupperware mold.
