This will serve at least 8 people.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nutmeg, and pour into a greased and floured 9-inch glass pie plate.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Forms its own crust.

title: rhubarb-pineapple salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cover and cook until tender (5 minutes).
Reserve juice of pineapple and rhubarb syrup.
Combine both syrups and add water to make 1 3/4 cups.
Heat to boiling. Add to gelatin and lemon juice.
When cool, fold in rhubarb and pineapple.

title: sausage party ryes
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese in microwave.
Combine sausage and cheese and spread on ryes.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: slow baking beef stew
directions: Place 2 pounds beef stew meat, cut into 1 1/4-inch cubes, in a pan 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inches.
Peel and slice 1 medium onion. Diagonally slice 1 stalk of celery.
Pare 6 carrots and cut into chunks.
Add vegetables to the baking pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and beaten eggs; add remaining ingredients and pour into the pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: scampi alla frank
directions: Ingredients can be altered to taste or portions.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, 1 stick margarine, vanilla and milk; pour into a greased casserole.
Mix brown sugar, flour, 1/2 stick margarine and nuts.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain well.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Cube bread and place in a sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer sausage and cheese.
Pour milk and egg mixture over top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: just like orange julius(serves 2 to 6)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
May substitute grape juice for orange juice.

title: apple pie
directions: Melt margarine; mix with egg, flour and sugar until creamy. Place apple pie filling in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan and place bread, with ends cut off, on top.
Pour mixture over bread and refrigerate overnight or at least 1 to 2 hours.

title: beef-n-cream
directions: *Cook in water until soft, about 2 hours.
Slice into 1/4-inch strips.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add milk and grated rind of lemon.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool.
While warm, drizzle glaze over top.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain juice from pickles; rinse with cold water.
Bring vinegar and sugar to boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Pour hot syrup over dill pickles.
Refrigerate overnight before using.
Keep refrigerated.

title: nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and milk.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder all at once.
Put in nuts.
Stir all at once.
Add vanilla.
Let rise for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Stir in egg yolks to sugar, cocoa and cornstarch mixture. Add small amount of milk; stir until smooth, then stir in remaining milk gradually. Bring to boil over low heat. Stir until thick. Remove from fire; blend in oleo and vanilla. Pour into pie shell. Top with meringue or Cool Whip when cool.

title: the family recipe tea
directions: The pot I use for iced tea holds 8 quarts.
Use any size you want and experiment with number of tea bags.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer Nilla Wafers and sliced bananas in deep dish baking bowl, ending with wafers.
Set aside.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt.
Mix in 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour over wafers and bananas.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually add remaining sugar.
Spread over top and brown in a 425° oven.

title: carrots supreme
directions: Peel and coarsely shred carrots.
Parboil in salted water until tender, but firm.
Drain well and
spread in shallow buttered dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Scatter bacon over top. Bake in moderate oven at 350°
until bacon is crisp, about 30 minutes.
About 6 servings.

title: memorial pie
directions: Beat the egg whites stiff.
Stir white sugar into egg whites. Crumble in the soda crackers.
Fold in baking powder and nuts. Put mixture into pie tin and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool, then add whipping cream or Cool Whip topping.
Let stand for several hours or overnight.

title: cheese straws
directions: Stir ingredients to form a soft dough. Shape into 2-inch sticks. Bake on cookie sheet at 450° for 7 minutes.

title: fricadellen
directions: Combine beef, onion, bread, 1/2 cup of water, 1/2 teaspoon of the salt, pepper and nutmeg in large bowl; mix well.
Shape into 4 loaves.
Cook loaves in hot oil in large skillet until browned. Stir in gravy and wine.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until cooked through.

title: chicken joyce
directions: Wrap chicken around with 2 or 3 pieces of beef.
Wrap bacon around chicken.
Cover with mixture of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Add almonds.
Cover with top or foil; bake in preheated oven at 300° for 3 hours, at 350° for 2 hours or at 250° for 4 hours.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Stew hen until done; remove hen and keep broth to use later.

title: tuna dip
directions: Blend all together in electric mixer.

title: caramel walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and egg. Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until crumbly. Stir in walnuts. Reserve 2 cups of crumb mixture and press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients except water, poppy seed and nuts, then add water, poppy seed and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 1 large loaf or 5 small loaves.

title: clarks favorite baked squash casserole
directions: Cook
squash
and
onion
in
a small amount of boiling water for
to	7
minutes or until squash is tender;
drain well. Place
vegetables in electric blender and process until smooth, then combine the squash mixture and remaining ingredients, mix well
and spoon into lightly greased 2 quart shallow casserole dish.
Bake
uncovered
for
minutes. Yields 8 servings.
Good.

title: cherry pink salad
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Then add all other ingredients except bananas.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with bananas just before serving.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with fork.
Make 3 holes and add liquid ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and ice.

title: makowiec(poppy seed roll)
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
In saucepan, heat and stir sour cream, butter, honey and salt until warm and butter almost melts. Turn into large mixing bowl.
Stir in 1 cup of flour; beat well. Add the softened yeast and eggs; stir until smooth.
Stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can mix in with a spoon.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp.
Mix cheese, butter and mayonnaise together in mixer.
Add other ingredients, except shrimp.
Shred shrimp by hand and mix with the other ingredients in the mixer.
Let set overnight.

title: maple bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Spread in prepared pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cut into squares while warm.

title: mr. d.'s meat loaf
directions: Shape into a loaf.
Brush the top with sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix first
ingredients with mixer on low speed.
Add flour, soda,
salt,
poppy
seed
and
evaporated milk and mix well. Fold in pecans.
Pour into an ungreased angel cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mary seward's chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs; mix.
Add buttermilk, hot water and vanilla.
Mixture will be very thin.

Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch layers (after greasing and flouring lightly) in a 350° oven until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted in the middle, approximately 40 minutes for the 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine ingredients as listed.
Spray pan with Pam.
Pour in mixture.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll on floured surface, 1/4-inch thick. Bake at 250° for 10 minutes until golden brown.
Yields 12 biscuits.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, egg, sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Beat well.
Add chocolate chips; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; beat well.
Line cupcake tin with papers; fill 1/3 full with chocolate batter.
Top each with a tablespoon of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
After cheese has melted, add the rest of the ingredients and stir.
Cool before refrigerating. Keeps in the refrigerator for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat the oil and cook the chicken in it until the chicken is golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except the spaghetti. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with spaghetti.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on the bottom of a baking dish, then spread chili beans, then sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 300° until cheese melts; serve with taco chips.

title: tofu loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: larry's secret hot wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips; pat dry.
Deep fry at 400° for 12 minutes or until completely cooked and crispy; drain.
Combine hot sauce and butter.
Spread wings in pan; pour sauce over wings.
Shake.
Serve warm.
Makes 24 to 30 pieces.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Cook chicken and cube.
Roll chicken pieces in crescent rolls. Mix soup with 1/2 can milk.
Pour over rolls in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: seas salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box with bouillon cubes and cooking oil.
Drain and cool.
In a large mixing bowl, combine macaroni with tuna fish, salmon, flounder, shrimp and salmon juice.
Mix well.
Add mayonnaise, relish, celery, celery seed, onion, mustard, Old Bay seasoning and salt.
Mix well together. Add sugar to taste.

title: lemon butter balls
directions: You will need round toothpicks.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Remove and chop.
Mix all other ingredients with chicken.
Place 1 pie crust in pie dish.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Use second pie crust as top.
Brush with egg to make top crust turn brown.
Serves 4-6.

title: stovepipe bread
directions: Add yeast to 1 1/2 cups flour; blend well.
Combine milk, oil, water, sugar and salt.
Heat on low heat until warm.
Add to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and beat until blended.
Gradually add the last 1 cup of flour.
Spoon into 2 well-greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Put on plastic lids; let rise in warm place until it reaches top; remove lids.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Cool 20 minutes and remove from cans.

title: island refresher
directions: In a large bowl combine all the ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Pat down in cake pan.
Mix remaining 3 ingredients (2 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese) and pour on top of cake mix mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and serve in round rye bread.

title: peach dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread peaches with juice on bottom of pan evenly.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Drizzle melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over mixture.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until cake is firm. Serve warm with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Beat eggs and add to margarine.
Mix and add sugar, coconut, raisins, nuts and vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake one hour at 300° or until light brown on top.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add stuffing mix to 1 stick melted margarine.
Put 1/2 stuffing mix in baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Mix soups together.
Pour over chicken.
Put remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake 30 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
(I usually use 3 large breasts instead of whole chicken.)

title: asparagus chicken supreme
directions: Bring water, onion, celery and garlic to boil in deep kettle. Add chicken pieces; cover and simmer until chicken is fork-tender. Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove chicken from broth; reserve broth.
Cool chicken, remove meat from skin and bones, breaking into large bite-size pieces.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry angel delight(low-fat)
directions: Cut or tear cake into 1/2-inch pieces to measure 8 cups. Place half of the cake cubes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 1/3 cup of pie filling and spread remaining over cake cubes.
Cover with rest of cake cubes.
Combine pudding, milk, sour cream and reserved cherry pie filling.
Spoon over cake cubes.
Cover and chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; turn into greased casserole.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop by teaspoon into hot oil.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Roll in a ball and roll in chopped mixed nuts.

title: cocktail meat balls(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onions, milk, egg and next four ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet and brown meat balls.
Remove fat from meat balls.
Heat sauce and jelly, stirring constantly.
Add meat balls and stir until thoroughly coated.
Then simmer 30 minutes in uncovered pan.

title: white trash
directions: In a large container, mix dry ingredients.
In a saucepan, slowly melt margarine, chocolate morsels and peanut butter, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.
Add vanilla and cool.
Pour sauce (about 1/3 at a time) over cereal mix and mix until well coated.
Pour into a large grocery bag and shake with the powdered sugar (about 1/2 box at a time).

title: mrs. dorsey's calico bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Place in large kettle.
Cover with water and salt.
Soak overnight.
Drain off water the next morning.
Add 6 cups of water.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir well.
Cook for another half hour.
Serve.

title: summertime cookies
directions: Cook sugar, butter, cocoa and milk 2 minutes after it comes to boil.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: carrot-apple casserole
directions: For 2 servings, halve ingredients.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onion, Italian seasoning and salt (it will be thick).
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes; stir often.
Place biscuits in greased muffin pan, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuit lined cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes 12 Pizza Cups.

title: smoked chicken on grill
directions: Preheat grill to 350°.
Place chicken halves (inside down) on cooking grid.
Baste with listed ingredients.
Turn chicken every 10 to 15 minutes, basting with sauce each time.
Takes about 1 1/2 hours.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Combine blackberries, water and 2 1/2 cups sugar in a large Dutch oven; stir well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Combine milk, 1 cup sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla in a large mixing bowl; mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder, stirring well. Gradually add flour mixture to milk mixture, stirring lightly until dry ingredients are moistened and a soft dough forms.

title: sunshine muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Makes 12 to 15 muffins.
Serve warm.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Pour bourbon over nuts and let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Cream confectioners sugar and butter.
Mix with hot nut mixture until crumbly.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Grease hands often with butter.
Form balls.
Set in freezer.
In the meantime, mix the chocolate covering.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and put in greased pan.
Place chicken over broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise and soup and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: do ahead mashed potatoes
directions: To roast a pepper, broil or grill it until it's black all over. Put the roasted pepper in a brown paper bag or wrap in newspaper. Seal tightly.
After 10 minutes or so, use a knife to peel off the skin and scrape away the seeds.
Cut the pepper into strips. To store (up to a month), cover with oil in a jar and refrigerate.

title: cucumber delight
directions: Combine vinegar, water, salt and sugar.
Bring to a boil and stir until sugar and salt dissolve.
Set aside to cool.
Wash, peel and slice cucumbers into rather thick pieces.
(Sometimes I don't peel my cucumbers and they are just as good.)
Place onion and garlic in a clean quart jar.
Add cucumber slices, filling to the top.
Fill jar with the vinegar mixture.
Put top in place. Refrigerate pickles for three days before serving.
Makes 1 quart.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour in pie crust and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough (which has been brought to room temperature) out on a pizza pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: easy candy peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips over hot water in a double boiler.
Stir to blend.
Add Spanish salted peanuts.
Mix together and drop by teaspoonfuls on an oiled cookie sheet.
Chill and enjoy.

title: 9th street house tea
directions: Mix together and add enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as on package. Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes, then poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add cold water and spoon over cake in pan. Chill 3 to 4 hours. Top with Cool Whip.

title: granny gossett's green salad
directions: Mix lime Jell-O with boiling water.
Add miniature marshmallows and cream cheese.
Stir this until all melts and is smooth.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Place this in refrigerator until slightly congealed.
Whip the whipping cream until it forms peaks and starts to stiffen.
Fold this into Jell-O mixture.
Pour into serving dish and refrigerate overnight.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sorghum cake
directions: Add soda to boiling water with lard to melt.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan until done.

title: amaretto coffee
directions: Combine coffee and Amaretto; stir well.
Top each serving with a dollop of cream.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve immediately.

title: oreo pudding
directions: Place 1 layer of Oreos in bottom of bowl, then 1 layer of chocolate pudding and then 1 layer of Cool Whip.
Continue repeating that same method until finished.
The last layer on top should be the Oreos.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Mix in top of double boiler marshmallows, butter, juice from maraschino cherries and peppermint candy.
Mash up as fine as possible.
Then mix following:
raisins, dates, pecans, maraschino cherries, cut up, and graham crackers, crushed fine.
When mixture is dissolved in double boiler, pour the liquid over the other ingredients and mix well.
Pack in buttered containers.

title: blueberry torte
directions: The festive flavors of pumpkin, pecans and spices create this showcase torte.

title: bridget's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in covered skillet with water until chicken is done.
Drain.
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.

title: taco salad
directions: Coat warm chicken chunks with taco mix.

title: very good casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: buttery lemon squares
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and the 1/2 cup powdered sugar until
light and fluffy. Add 2 cups of flour and beat until blended. Spread evenly in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: batter for u.f.o.'s(unidentified frying objects)
directions: Dust prepared food with flour.
Shake off excess flour.
Using tong, dip food into batter, letting excess drip off.
Lower into hot (375°) corn oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with corn flakes mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Mix and put in large container.
Let set 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: easy bake chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl, mix three types of soup and add two soup cans of milk and Lipton onion soup mix.
Pour cup of uncooked rice over butter in pan, then pour soup mixture over rice.
Push chicken down into rice.
Cover with foil and cook two hours.
Take foil off the last ten minutes of cooking time.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat and drain. Mix dry ingredients in large bowl. Cut onion into quarters and add to eggs, milk and peppers in the blender. Mix until onions and peppers are minced fine. Grate cheese. Pour liquid into dry ingredients. Add meat, corn and cheese. Add oil and mix thoroughly. Bake in shallow pan (cake pan) 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in oven.
Take out of oven; let cool.
Make layers:
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on bottom of pan.
Layer chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour milk on top.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Press with hands, lightly.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: creamy crab and pasta
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, prepare rigatoni according to package directions.
Add broccoli, carrot, green onions and red pepper the last five minutes of cooking time.
Drain.

title: brown bread
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over the list of ingredients, except the egg and flour.
Let stand about 8 hours.
Add the egg and flour (same bowl).
Pour into greased loaf pan or tin cans. Excellent with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix
ingredients
in
order
in
a large bowl.	You may chill and slice or drop by teaspoon on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350°
for 8	to 10 minutes.	Doubles easily and freezes well, both before and after baking.

title: grandma's lemon cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar. Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to shortening mixture alternating milk.
Mix well, beating 2 minutes. Add vanilla and fold in the egg whites.
Bake in 2 or 3 layer pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin with marinade
directions: Mix together and put in plastic bag with tenderloin and seal. Refrigerate over night. Grill 14-20 minutes or until done.

title: pink arctic freeze salad
directions: Cream together cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Fold in cranberry sauce, pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into square Pyrex or plastic container and put in freezer.
Serve on shredded lettuce.
Best eaten partially frozen.

title: lib's cheese ball
directions: Mix together the 3 cheeses, pecans, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce. Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste. Shape into 4 small cheese balls and sprinkle with paprika. Cheese balls freeze well.

title: noodle and kraut bake
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine until translucent. Rinse sauerkraut under running water and gently squeeze out water. Add sauerkraut and onion soup mix to pan with onion and mushrooms.
Mix well and saute for 5 minutes.
Make noodles according to package directions.
Combine drained noodles and ingredients from pan in large casserole dish.
Place in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chew bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; blend in eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, milk and sauce.
Stir until sauce and milk are absorbed; the mixture should be creamy.
Mix shredded dried beef, onions and garlic.
Form into a ball; add some beef to outside of cheese ball.
Refrigerate overnight or for at least 4 hours.

title: bubble bread
directions: Spray a Bundt pan with nonstick spray.
Tear loaf into pieces (about 15 pieces) and place in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix on top of bread.
Crumble brown sugar on top.
Cut oleo into pats and place on top.
Cover with towel and let rise overnight.
Next morning, remove towel.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potatoes royal
directions: Peel cooled potatoes and cut into halves or thirds lengthwise. Add salt, if necessary.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, heat slowly and pour over potatoes.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven, basting frequently with sauce in pan. Serves 6.

title: kersten's chocolate truffle
directions: Looks nice in a truffle bowl.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a punch bowl.
Yield:
3 1/2 quarts.

title: cracklin cornbread
directions: Mix well the cornmeal, egg, Crisco and milk until smooth and damp consistency.
Add cracklings and mix well.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease large casserole dish (I use a large cast-iron skillet.)
Pour mixture into dish and cook 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: red beet cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar, vanilla and almond extract.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture, a little at a time, beating well.
Fold beets, coconut and crushed pineapple into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or frosting.

title: roasted chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place into cooking pot.
Cover and cook 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix remaining egg white, yolks, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese until creamy.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 can of rolls on bottom of pan.
Spread creamed mixture on top.
Put other can over. Perforate with fork.
Spread with 2 tablespoons egg whites.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, pecans and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch(50 cups)
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with recommended sugar.
Add pineapple juice, ginger ale and enough sherbet for taste and decoration.

title: crusty coconut pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs; beat well.
Add milk, coconut and flavoring.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown and firm.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water until dissolved.
Add orange sherbet.
Mix together oranges, pineapple and bananas; add to jello mixture.
Chill.

title: sloppy joes for 50
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add soups, ketchup, mustard and chili powder.
Cook for 1 hour only in large kettle, stirring frequently as mixture will thicken.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and shortening to a boil; add dry ingredients. Stir until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Cool slightly.
Add beaten eggs, one at a time.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and fill with custard filling.

title: puppy chow
directions: You will need a large mixing bowl and 1 paper grocery bag.

title: helen's banana bread
directions: Line loaf pan with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars, peanut butter and eggs.
Add vanilla, syrup and soda.
Gradually add oats and finally fold in M&M's. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes. Makes 12 dozen.

title: "boursin" cheese
directions: Allow cream cheese and butter to soften.
When soft, mix the rest of the ingredients with the butter and cream cheese and refrigerate.
Makes 3 cups.

title: plain and simple carrot cake
directions: Beat together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add carrots and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost when cool with the following icing.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Add eggs. Stir, then add milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. When thickened, add flavoring. Layer wafers, bananas and sugar mixture. Beat egg whites and a dash of salt until fluffy. Add to top of mixture, then put in oven and brown top on broil.

title: basic butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Spoon cookie dough onto cookie sheet and flatten dough with a wet fork.
Bake cookies at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serves 25 people.

title: chocolate-black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar very well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and chocolate and fold in walnuts.
Turn into Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mud balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs and eat!

title: peanut butter cup
directions: Mix well with hands until smooth. Roll into small balls and place on wax paper. Place in refrigerator until cool and firm. Meanwhile, melt 2 (12 ounce) packages chocolate chips and a block of paraffin wax in a double boiler (water in bottom pan). Roll balls in mixture and place back in refrigerator until cool. Better if kept in a cool place. Yields 100.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Crumble potato chips with butterscotch pieces and mix all in mixer.
Add eggs, vanilla and butter flavor.
Combine and add a little at a time the flour, soda and salt.
Bake until light brown at 350°.

title: orange jello tapioca salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
Add drained fruit cocktail.
Chill until set.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Steam about 2 to 3 hours. Steam in greased and floured tin cans.
Makes over three regular sized cans.
Fill about 2/3 full.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cook onion in boiling water until tender.
Do not drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato puree, garlic, oregano, celery seed and pepper to onion.
Simmer for 10 minutes to blend flavors.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stir-fry chicken in olive oil until done (not pink in center). Mix all ingredients except cheese, paprika and cracker crumbs. Blend well.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes (longer if frozen).
During last 10 minutes garnish with buttered cracker crumbs, cheese and paprika.
Yields 8 servings.

title: squash casserole (yellow)
directions: Mix all together with cooked squash and bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: baked turkey
directions: Wash thawed turkey and salt well inside and out.
Stuff with apple (quartered), 1 large onion (quartered), celery stalks (cut in 2-inch lengths) and the 6 tablespoons margarine.
Tie the legs together securely.
Place in enamel roasting pan, breast side up. Sprinkle top lightly with sugar and dot with 4 tablespoons margarine.
Add enough water to make 1/4-inch in bottom of pan. Cover and bake at 350° for time recommended on turkey.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice beef in 1/2-inch strips, long and thin as possible. Pour the 1/4 cup soy sauce and sugar over meat and marinate for 1/2 hour.
Meantime, cut the tomatoes and pepper in 1-inch cubes. Heat oil in large skillet.
Add garlic and ginger.
After a minute, remove garlic and add peppers.
Saute for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally so ingredients will cook evenly.
Add beef and cook an additional 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and blend cornstarch with remaining soy sauce.
Stir into mixture.
Cook, stirring gently for another minute.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: built-in sandwich bread
directions: Stir yeast into warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes and stir well.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir in flour.
Knead on a well-floured board until dough is elastic (about 5 minutes). Cover and let rise until double in size.
With fingers, knead in rest of ingredients making certain it is well distributed and covered with dough.
Divide dough and shape into two loaves.
Put into greased pans (8 x 5 x 3-inch).
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until crusty and brown. Cool on rack.

title: orange circus peanut salad
directions: Stir until dissolved and add 1 cup crushed pineapple, drained. When jello starts to jell, stir in 1 large Cool Whip.

title: spicy chicken and rice
directions: Season chicken.
In large skillet, saute onion and garlic 2 minutes.
Add picante and broth; bring to boil.
Add rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand until liquid is gone.
Serve with avocado, tomato and cheese on top.
May serve with olives and sour cream, if desired.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Pour over ice.
Refreshing on a hot summer day.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water. Combine soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and ginger.
Stir into bouillon mixture.
In large skillet brown chicken in oil.
Add bouillon mixture.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients except cashews and rice.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Remove from heat.
Add cashews and serve over rice.

title: cheese and rice souffle
directions: Grease casserole dish, heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter, stir in flour and add milk; cook until thickened.
Add sliced or grated cheese.
Separate 4 eggs.
To yolks, add 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper, beat them with fork and add to cheese mixture.
Add rice. Next, fold into stiff egg whites.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: stove top scampi
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add butter and garlic.
Saute for 2 minutes, carefully coating pan.
Place shrimp in pan; brown on one side and turn, then sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with vermouth.
Swirl shrimp and seasonings together.
Turn off heat and cover.
Serve immediately.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and shortening.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth, about 1 minute.
Bake in greased 8-inch square baking pan in preheated hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana ham patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well; form into 6 patties. Place on foil lined baking sheet; broil for 5 minutes on each side.
Serve with additional mustard.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix Ritz crackers with 1/2 stick margarine and set aside. Cook broccoli and drain well.
Mix second 1/2 stick margarine with Velveeta and toss with broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet and sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vinegar and oil to make dressing.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Coat cut up chicken in a mixture of the flour, salt and paprika.
Brown chicken in 1/2 cup shortening.
After chicken has browned, lay it in a casserole dish.
Stir into a bowl the dried onion soup and dried chicken noodle soup and mix with 2 cups water. Pour liquid mixture over browned chicken.
Put into oven and bake at 350°, covered, 30 minutes.
After chicken is baked; remove chicken to platter.
Stir the evaporated milk and poultry seasoning into juices.
Add chicken and bake until thickened.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain. Combine all ingredients in large kettle. Cook over medium heat for 1 hour. Soup is better next day.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown meat; saute onion and garlic.
Mix all ingredients. Cook about 1 hour.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Cook hominy with salt, pepper and bacon grease until most of juice is gone; drain.
Add mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and onion. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain well and mix in egg, onion soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour into lightly buttered dish and top with the crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, mix in applesauce.
Add flour mixed with baking soda, cinnamon,
nutmeg and salt.
Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Spread batter in greased 15 x 10-inch drip pan.

title: joy's sponge cake
directions: Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, baking
powder and salt. Beat egg whites at high speed until frothy.
Add cream of tartar. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stiff but not dry peaks form.
Combine egg yolks, water, vanilla and dry ingredients. Beat at medium-high speed until thick and lemon-colored (about 4 minutes).
Gradually fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites.
Pour batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes or until cake tests firm.
Invert tube pan on funnel to bottle to cool.
When completely cooled, remove from pan.

title: favorite baked beans(servings:  6 to 8)
directions: Bake in greased casserole, uncovered, for 2 1/2 hours at 325°. Can be made day before and then just cooked.
If it's refrigerated, allow 3 hours to bake.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until well blended. Gradually add combined flour, baking soda and salt, mixing well. Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar, egg, shortening and vanilla, beating thoroughly.
Sift together the flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix dry ingredients alternately with sour milk to first mixture.
Mix until stiff dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Put all dry ingredients in a bowl (cornmeal, flour, soda, salt, sugar.)
Stir well; add wet ingredients to first mixture; onion, buttermilk, egg, and cheese.
Stir well.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients and make a ball.
Roll in reserved nuts.
Leave in the refrigerator at least 4 hours before serving.

title: lemon cloud pie(five minutes to make)
directions: Stir the lemon curd until it's smooth.
Whip the cream until it doubles in volume and forms soft peaks.
Gently stir a large spoonful of the whipped cream into the lemon curd to lighten it. Then fold in the remaining whipped cream.
Spoon the lemon filling into the prepared crust.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni. Cut bacon into 1 inch pieces. Cube Velveeta cheese. Layer macaroni, cheese, tomatoes, and bacon. Keep layering until casserole is full. Last layer should be bacon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Gradually add sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla; mix well.
Add water.
Beat with mixer until firm.
Enough for 2-layer cake.

title: hilda's little hennies(when i made these in my cafeteria, they always went fast.)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, shortening and milk together in a medium sized bowl.
Break dough into sections and form small balls.
Mix melted butter with cinnamon and sugar mixture in a small bowl.
Roll dough balls in this mixture, then place on a lightly greased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp and cheese fettuccine
directions: Saute shrimp, onion and green onions until shrimp is pink and onions are soft.
While this is cooking, boil water for noodles. After shrimp and seasonings are cooked, add Pet milk and 2 cheeses, chopped in squares, to mixture.
Cook until cheeses are melted and mixture is creamy (about 15 minutes on low so mixture doesn't burn).
Boil noodles while mixture is cooking.
Drain noodles, then mix noodles with the shrimp and cheese mixture.
Cook an additional 5 minutes, stirring so doesn't stick.
Serve with French bread as a side item.
Serves 4.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, shortening, milk, vanilla, egg whites and 1 cup coconut.
Blend 2 minutes at low speed, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Put everything into the blender; blend on high until it's slushy.
Don't even think of trying any other recipe for Orange Julius, because this is the best!

title: corned beef and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together, except cheese.
Put in buttered, shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: company chicken
directions: Salt and garlic salt the chicken pieces a bit, then paprika it thoroughly.
Spread chicken out in one layer in a shallow baking pan.
Dilute the soup with the cream; pour it over the chicken. Sprinkle the chopped parsley (generously) on the top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and Jello (dry). Melt marshmallows in pan with 7-up. Combine together, then add pineapple.
Chill until slightly jelled (about 30 minutes). Take out of Refrigerator and add 1/2 of pecans and Cool Whip.
Whip all together. Place remaining pecans on top.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add butter and milk.
Roll and slice into 1/2-inch thick portions.
Cook at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. To drop, add 1/4 cup milk extra.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients except for apples and nuts.
Fold in apples and nuts with spoon.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream and horseradish sauce in a bowl.
Mix the chicken, celery and cashews.
Pour the first mixture over chicken mixture; mix well.
Top with paprika.
Chill. Serves 4 to 5.

title: cheese and broccoli stuffed pasta
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Cook broccoli as directed on package and chop fine.
Melt butter or margarine and add onions, basil, oregano and salt.
Cook until onions are done.
Add broccoli, stirring to blend.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add milk. Stir and heat to boiling, until thickened.
Stir in shredded cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan.
Fill shells (about 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per shell) and put in buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and drizzle with cream.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat and sauce.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain.
Blend Ricotta cheese with egg and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread about 1/2 cup sauce; over this, layer 1/3 of noodles, half of Ricotta cheese mixture and 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with sauce; sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Repeat.
Top with remaining noodles; cover generously with sauce and remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot beef "en daube"
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes.

Put everything in crock-pot, except cornstarch. Cover and cook on low 8 hours. After first 30 minutes, stir to break up bouillon cube if you are still home (or use powdered bouillon or just add it at the end).

title: easy lemon freeze
directions: In small pan, melt margarine; stir in crumbs, reserving 2 tablespoons for garnish.
Pat crumbs on bottom of buttered 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine pie filling, sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Mix until smooth. Spread into prepared pan.
Top with whipped topping and reserved crumbs.
Freeze 3 to 4 hours.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add sharp cheese, onions, Worcestershire, lemon juice, mustard, paprika, salt, ham, parsley and pimento.
Mix well.
Chill until nearly firm.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts.
Wrap in foil.
Chill overnight.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Slice to serve.
Could be made into a log.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef in oil, drain off oil.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Blend flour and water; four over mixture and stir.
Add worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Stir and simmer 15 minutes. Serve on a bun with cole slaw.

title: one bowl holiday fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large, microwavable bowl on High for 2 to 3 minutes, or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Remove from microwave; stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in an 8-inch square greased pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix together all ingredients and make into balls.
Chill.

title: tuna supreme
directions: While cooking the macaroni, in a large bowl, mix together the mushroom soup, mushroom pieces (undrained), tuna (undrained), peas, sour cream, 1 cup of the shredded Cheddar cheese and the cheese packet.
Once the macaroni is cooked, drain and add to other ingredients.
This mixture is enough for two (2) casseroles or one (1) large oven dish.

title: oil pastry(pie crust)
directions: Combine flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Put oil and water in a jar and shake vigorously.
Pour this mixture over the flour and mix with a fork to form a ball.
Divide in half for 2 single or 1 double crust pie.
Roll between 2 sheets of waxed paper.

title: mango salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water; add sugar. In a separate bowl, blend mango, juice and cream cheese. (Can use blender.)
Add the jello mixture and 1 cup cold water. Pour into mold or dish. Chill. When firm, top each serving with Cool Whip and pecans.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat after each addition.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk. Add flavoring.
Pour in tube pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar. Put in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool 1 hour. Beat with electric mixer the sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese. Spread over cooled pretzels. Mix strawberry Jell-O and boiling
water and let stand for 10 minutes. Pour over cheese mixture and refrigerate.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, pepper and celery; cook until sauce has thickened.
Cook spaghetti according to box.
Add to sauce. Put in large baking dish(es).
Top with grated cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread crumbs in greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Set aside.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Place over bread. Add ham.
Mix cheeses and flour.
Place over ham.
Combine milk, eggs, mustard and garlic salt, mixing well.
Pour over cheese. Chill 8 hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: lizard tails
directions: Slice cucumbers lengthwise.
Pack in jars.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to boil.
Let cool to lukewarm and pour over cucumbers.
Put in cold pack; add cold water to cover jars.
Just bring to boil and remove jars immediately.

title: cheese dip
directions: Fry hamburger meat and sausage.
Drain and place in a large glass dish.
Combine the remaining ingredients in the removable dish from crock-pot.
Heat until all cheese is melted.
Add meat and keep in crock-pot on low heat.
Serve over corn chips.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples and cut into eight wedges each. Place one wedge on each unrolled crescent roll and wrap large end to small end. Place each roll in a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish. Melt margarine and mix with sugar and cinnamon. Pour over dumplings; then pour Mt. Dew over the dumplings and sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: danish puffs
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients like pie crust.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bring the 1/2 cup margarine and water to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add 1 cup flour quickly.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well between each egg. Spread evenly on crust.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350° until light brown.
Cool.
Frost with thin layer of powdered sugar frosting.

title: dad's stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers and cut off tops.
(Save tops, minus stems, for filling.)
Combine celery, onion, and diced pepper top pieces and saute in a skillet.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans in top of double boiler; bring water to boil.
Reduce heat; cook, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans. Quickly spread mixture into a lightly buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans.
Chill.
Cut into squares. Store in refrigerator.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen squares.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Add milk and berry preserves.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture. Last of all add vanilla and 1 1/2 teaspoons soda dissolved in 1/2 cup hot water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Follow ingredients on back of cake mix box.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan (not all the batter) and bake.

title: shabu shabu
directions: Mix Tare ahead of
time to pour in individual bowls per serving.

title: orange sherbet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients.
Bake in 2 or 3 (9-inch) cake pans for 30 minutes (or 20 minutes if 3 pans are used) until done.
Cool layers completely.
Layers can be split, if desired.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Put tomatoes, onions and peppers in a large pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over them.
Remove from heat immediately and put in sterile jars and seal.

title: boston cream pie
directions: Beat pudding mix with 1 cup milk as directed on package for 2 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread half of pudding mixture between cake layers.
Serve remainder as pudding.
Spread top layer with thin chocolate icing.

title: chicken and potatoes
directions: Toss cut up chicken and potatoes with some oil.
Add spices. Put in casserole dish and bake in oven at 375° for 1 hour.

title: three cheese lasagna rolls(children's section recipe)
directions: About 2 hours before serving, in boiling, salted water, cook lasagna noodles as label directs; drain and cool.
Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, thoroughly mix Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan, egg, salt and oregano.
Cut lasagna noodles in half crosswise.
On each half, evenly spread 1/4 cup cheese mixture.
Roll up each noodle, jellyroll fashion.
Spoon 1 cup spaghetti sauce into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange rolls on sauce in a single layer; top with remaining sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together, except oleo and chicken.
Dry chicken pieces.
Dip in oleo; roll in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish, skin side up.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until tender.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach, pressing against sides of sieve until all moisture is removed.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours for full flavor development.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients with dollop of butter on top.
Bake in oven until pudding mix is thick, about 45 minutes at 400°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except meat and cheese, in a casserole dish.
Place meat patties in the mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Put cheese on top when almost done.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Filling: Mix all ingredients except the potatoes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soften bread crumbs in milk.
Add beef, nutmeg, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix and form into balls.
Brown meatballs in broiler. Remove meatballs and place in large saucepan.
Brown onions in skillet and add onions and soup mixes to saucepan.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: slow cooker dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
In slow cooker, combine hamburger, Velveeta cheese, salsa and black olives.
Stir to melt cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Mix
brown
sugar
and
whipping
cream
in large glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 14 minutes, stirring after 7 minutes.
Remove
and add pecans, butter and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on foil (do not use waxed paper).
Makes 3 dozen small or 2 dozen medium.
Do not try to double recipe.

title: soft pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, pumpkin, shortening and orange peel.
Stir in dry ingredients, then add raisins and nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat well. Add flour, cornmeal and vanilla.
Pour into two unbaked 8 or 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: caramel oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan; dust with flour.
Put rolled oats into medium bowl; set aside.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chips over very low heat.
Mix until smooth and pour over cereal; mix well.
Place powdered sugar in a paper bag.
Add the chocolate-covered cereal and toss and shake well.

title: hawaiian pot roast
directions: In kettle or Dutch oven, brown the meat in oil.
Remove and pour off fat.
Add soy sauce, water, pepper, ginger and onion. Place meat in pot and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer, turning several times and adding a little water if necessary for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add mushrooms, celery and pineapple chunks and cook 15 minutes longer or until celery is tender but still crisp.
Remove meat.
If dry, add more water.
Mix cornstarch with a little cold water and add to vegetables.
Cook, stirring until thickened.

title: steak and mushroom casserole
directions: Brown steak in drippings.
Remove steaks from pan and saute onions and mushroom slices until tender.
Drain steak, onions and mushrooms on absorbent paper.
Combine soup, buttermilk, parsley and seasonings.
Place alternate layers of potatoes, onions and mushroom slices and steaks in a 2 1/2-quart greased casserole. Pour a little soup mixture on each layer.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 350° oven for one hour.
Makes four servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together with slim and trim mayonnaise to moisten.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ground chuck, bell pepper, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until done.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vegetables; blend well. Chill.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with your choice of vegetables.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, salt, 1/3 cup sugar and 2 cups milk in double boiler until all the milk is absorbed.
Heat 2 cups milk and add 1/4 cup sugar, vanilla and raisins until boiling point.
Beat eggs and stir into rice mixture along with milk mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Wash beans. Place in a large pot. Add water, about 1-inch above beans; salt. Can add small piece of salt pork to season. Cook until tender; just watch and add water as needed. Brown hamburger; drain. Add hamburger, onion and crushed tomatoes to beans. Cook for another 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Stir soup mix, soup and rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Add water and stir.
Place meat on top, then cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peppered tenderloin of beef(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat the oven to 425°.
Oil a roasting pan.
Combine the peppercorns, coriander and salt; grind coarsely.
Rub the beef with the 1/2 tablespoon oil and roll in the peppercorn mixture to coat evenly.
Roast 25 minutes or internal temperature of 125° for rare, 30 to 35 minutes or internal temperature of 130° to 135° for medium-rare, or 40 minutes or an internal temperature of 140° for medium.
Let tenderloin stand 10 minutes before carving into thick or thin slices.
Serve with creamed horseradish sauce on the side.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking soda.
In large bowl, mix margarine, sweetener and egg. Mix dry ingredients, alternating with applesauce.
Fold in bran, nuts and raisins.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by tablespoon. Lightly flatten with fork dipped in milk.
Bake 7 or 8 minutes. Yields 36 large cookies.

title: sour cream dip for strawberries
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with whole strawberries whose stems and caps have been left intact.

title: layered chicken salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Place lettuce in the bottom of a 4-quart salad bowl. Layer with cucumber, jicama, onions, pea pods and chicken. In a small bowl combine mayonnaise, sugar, curry and ginger. Spread over the top of salad.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and mustard in a small bowl. Measure out 1/3 cup and refrigerate.
With remaining mixture, brush both sides of chicken.
Coat well with crumbs.
Arrange in lightly greased shallow baking pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes or until cooked through.
Serve with reserved mayonnaise mixture for dipping.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Beat egg, sugar, oil and vanilla together until fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients:
flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa.
Pour in remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan (greased). Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Finely chop green pepper and mix with cream cheese, milk, chipped beef, onion, sour cream and garlic.
In a pan, saute pecans, butter and salt.
Spread pecan mixture over beef mixture and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or longer if dip has been refrigerated.

title: honey chicken
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Add other ingredients and mix. Roll chicken pieces in mixture and baste during baking.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight before serving.
Will keep several days in the refrigerator.

title: fresh carrot soup
directions: Cook and stir bacon, onion and garlic in large saucepan until bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered until vegetables are tender; 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour mixture into blender and cover.
Blend on high until smooth.
If thinner consistency is desired, stir in water or chicken broth.
Garnish with sour cream, snipped parsley or shredded carrot, if desired.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper until smooth.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes, or until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 2 cups of cheese until melted.
Turn macaroni into greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour cheese mixture over macaroni; mix well.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp in lemon butter
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add next 8 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until done.
Garnish with lemon wedges, if desired.

title: chocolate bar pie
directions: Put milk and marshmallows into top of double boiler. Stir constantly until marshmallows are melted. Break almond bars into this mixture. Stir until candy is melted and mixture is well blended.
Remove from heat and cool.
Whip the cream until thick. Fold whipped cream into cooled chocolate mixture, blending well. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over top of pie. Chill several hours before serving.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut each breast in half and pound with mallet until 1/2-inch thick.
In shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs with Parmesan.
Place egg in another shallow bowl.
Dip chicken pieces first into egg and then into crumb mixture until coated.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Drain and flake tuna, then add all ingredients.
Mix well. Serve on lettuce.
Garnish with sliced, hard-cooked eggs and parsley.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Mix with spaghetti sauce and pour into a casserole dish.
Spread sour cream over the mixture.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese.
Lay crescent rolls on top (without separating into triangles).
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles.
Chill.
Just before serving, add Chinese noodles.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Mix turnip with egg yolks, onion, sugar, salt, pepper and butter.
Whip egg whites and add to turnip mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Great served as a Thanksgiving casserole!
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice.
Add coconut, pecans and pineapple.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with cherries. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add taco and picante sauce. Top with refried beans, then sour cream, then cheese. Heat in oven to melt cheese.
Serve as main dish with salad or as dip with tortilla chips.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Make batter with flour, egg whites and nonfat milk.
Dip pieces into batter.
Either saute in pan or bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Put onto platter. Spread with spaghetti sauce and shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Put back in oven to melt cheese.
Serve with brown rice and steamed broccoli.

title: twist trio salad
directions: First, boil water to thoroughly cook noodles, then set aside to cool.
Cut up lettuce, cucumber, pepper, carrots, onions and broccoli.
Toss all into one bowl.
Add the cooled off noodles. Then cut (slice) the eggs.
Add olives to the salad and add as much Italian dressing as needed.
Top salad off with the sliced eggs for decoration.

title: rolled rib roast of beef or prime rib roast
directions: Rub salt and other ingredients on all parts of roast.
Place, uncovered, fat side up in a roasting pan.
Bake at 325° to desired doneness.
Let stand 15 minutes to firm meat before carving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Take out of oven.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Bake
cake
mix like box instructs.
Melt the marshmallows with
small
amount of 1 cup of milk.
When the marshmallows melt, add the remaining milk and 1 cup sugar.
Stir well. Remove from heat and add bag of coconut.
Pour on warm cake.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake like directed on box.
When cake is done, take end of silver dinner fork and punch holes in cake (not end with prongs).
Mix cream of coconut and condensed milk.
Spread on cake while still hot and let set about 2 hours or overnight.
Spread Cool Whip on top of cake.
Sprinkle coconut on cake.
Put in refrigerator.
Will keep about a week.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and stir in stuffing.
Put 1/2 of mixture in buttered baking dish.
Spread chicken (cut in bite size pieces) over this (use scissors for easy cutting).
Pour over the chicken 1 1/2 cups reserved broth.

title: tuna turnovers
directions: Combine ingredients, except rolls and cheese.
Form 8 rectangles by sealing perforated edges of 2 rolls.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cheese over half of each rectangle.
Top with about 1/4 cup of tuna mixture and another tablespoon of cheese.
Fold other half of rectangle over filling; seal edges with tines of fork. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: thai beef salad
directions: Wash cilantro; cut off leaves.
Mince stems with garlic and salt plus a little water to make a paste.
Spread on meat.
Cover and marinate at least 40 minutes, 2 hours is better.
Slice thin; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Fry in a little oil on high heat until done.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef on top of stove in a large roasting pan. Drain off any grease. Add all other ingredients; simmer slow for 1 hour.

title: shrimp souffle
directions: Grease a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Cut bread and cheese in quarters.
Layer bread, shrimp, cheese and one-half of the melted butter.
Repeat layers.

title: baked chicken salad pie
directions: Mix together chicken, celery, almonds, salt, onion, lemon juice, mayonnaise and water chestnuts.
Turn into a 10-inch fluted pie crust.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until crust is browned.
Add cheese and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: terry's crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: creamy ham and cheese salad
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Add additional salad dressing before serving, if desired.

title: banana and pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice.
Mix pineapple and bananas in salad bowl, set aside.
In saucepan, mix pineapple juice, sugar, eggs, margarine and flour; cook over medium heat until thick. Pour over bananas and pineapple.
Mix and serve.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and sugar in a large bowl.
Make well in center. Add eggs and oil, stirring until moistened. Carefully stir in strawberries and nuts. Pour into 8-inch greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat oil and sugar at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating one minute after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Stir remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture.
Add apples and nutmeats.
Batter will be very stiff.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients and divide evenly between the tortillas.
Spread and roll up.
Refrigerate for several hours, covered.
Slice 1/2-inch thick and serve.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together in large bowl. Bake as you do other bread. I bake in an iron skillet at 450 degrees for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: green salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Mix in cream cheese; add reserved pineapple liquid and cold water to equal 2 cups.
Chill until set, then add pecans and pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in warm water in a large bowl, stirring well.
Let stand 5 minutes until bubbly.
Add remaining sugar, shortening, baking powder, salt and 2 cups flour. Beat at low speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm place for 1 hour, until doubled in size.
Punch down dough; turn onto a lightly floured surface.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add carrots, vanilla and oil mixture together.
Add nut meats.
Stir lightly. Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add other ingredients, mixing well until creamy.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet by spoon. Bake about 7 minutes at 400°.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Boil together the sugar, water and shortening, salt, raisins, and spices for 5 minutes. When cooled add flour, soda is dissolved in teaspoon hot water. This makes two loaves. Bake about 45 minutes at 325. This cake is of good texture and will keep moist for some time.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix pork and beans, brown sugar, mustard, onion and ketchup in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place bacon slices on top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until the bacon is done.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix chocolate chips, oleo and butter together.
Melt.
Pour over Crispix or Chex and stir gently to coat cereal.
Place powdered sugar in large grocery bag and dump in cereal mixture. Shake to coat.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.
You may sift more powdered sugar on after it cools.

title: carnation meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomato sauce, and mix lightly. Place in baking dish and pour tomato sauce over meat loaf.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan to serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off of pineapple and slice bananas in it.
Let set about 5 minutes.
Stir in the pudding.
Stir in well drained fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks.

title: pizza bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Flatten 1 1/2 loaves of bread on baking sheet.
Put Pizza Quick in center of bread. Spread out pepperoni.
Put cheese on pepperoni.
Fold sides over ends.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix preceding and spoon over chicken.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 370°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix sugar, ginger, garlic and oil in a large bowl.
Add water, soy sauce and pineapple juice and mix well.
Add chicken wings and let marinate overnight.
Put chicken wings on rack and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: south carolina chews
directions: Cream the butter until smooth.
Add the brown sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix until crumbly.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Spread in a greased and floured 14 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over the chews while warm.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: In blender, combine yogurt, milk and Equal.
Add berries a few at a time through opening in lid.
Blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes through opening in lid, blending until slushy.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 82 calories.
Food Exchange:
1/2 Milk, 1 Fruit.

title: creamy  chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion until tender. Remove from heat. Add soup, tomatoes, sour cream, 3/4 c. cheddar cheese, 3/4 c. mozzarella cheese, mix well. Place 3 Tbsp. on each tortilla. Roll up tightly. Place seam side down in a 9x13 baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Top with remaining soup mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheeses. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes until heated through.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Remove seeds from squash and slice.
Chop onions and peppers. Sprinkle salt over squash, onions and peppers.
Mix together; let set overnight.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and stir in cornmeal.
Melt butter; add egg and milk and combine well.
Stir liquid ingredients into dry and combine just until moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix and blend everything except carrots.
When well mixed, add carrots.
Pour into oblong pan and bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
When cool, frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: impossible coconut custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan and let stand 5 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Servings:

title: olive parmesan potato topper
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and Parmesan cheese. Stir in olives, red pepper, onions and ground pepper.
Serve as a topper with baked potatoes or as a dip with assorted vegetables.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Follow Basic Biscuits recipe.
Roll dough out 1/4-inch thick and cut with doughnut cutter.
Dip biscuits in melted butter and then in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Twist once.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Peel apples and set aside.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Do not mix with apples.

title: crunchy potato balls
directions: In a bowl, combine the potatoes, ham, cheese, mayonnaise, egg, mustard and pepper; mix well.
Add enough of the flour to make a stiff mixture.
Chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in cornflakes.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes about 3 dozen.
Recipe may be doubled.
Good way to utilize mashed potatoes (leftover).

title: coconut pralines
directions: Boil sugar and milk to 240° on candy thermometer or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in coconut, pecans and butter.
Return to heat and continue cooking, stirring constantly, until candy returns to soft ball stage.
Beat until slightly thickened, but not until it loses its gloss.
Add vanilla.
Cook 3 minutes.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto double thickness of buttered waxed paper.
Yields 24 pralines.

title: my molded salad
directions: Pour
boiling water over Jell-O; blend.
Add 1 cup cold water. Refrigerate until set.
Add and mix in grated carrots, chopped nuts
and
raisins.
Pour into mold and let set.
Can make the day before you intend to use it.
As salad can serve with mayonnaise or plain.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix in casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and scallions.
Drain off fat.
Add refried beans and enchilada sauce.
Cook over medium heat for about 15 minutes.
In a baking pan, cover bottom of pan with a little meat mixture.
Then layer with tortillas.
(Just enough to cover pan.) Then layer with meat mixture and then cheeses.
Repeat, layering tortillas, meat mixture and cheeses.
You will have 2 layers of tortillas and your top layer will be cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
You can serve with sour cream and Guacamole.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Place crackers in a gallon bag.
Pour oil over crackers and toss to coat.
Add dressing mix.
Toss again.
Place in a baking pan, and bake at 250° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.

title: microwave italian nachos
directions: Place chips in a single layer on paper plate.
Top with Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni, Parmesan cheese and olives.
Put sauce in custard cup or small microwave-safe bowl; cover.
Cook on High about 45 to 60 seconds.
Serve pizza sauce for dip for the nachos.
Makes 1 serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients well.
Stir into vegetable ingredients. Marinate overnight or longer.
This salad improves with age.

title: mandy's cheese and beef pizza
directions: Look up Pizza Hut's phone number in the telephone directory, dial number, order pizza and wait 30 minutes for delivery.
Enjoy!

title: spinach dip
directions: Chop spinach and mix with other ingredients.

title: chicken epercurine
directions: Sear the chicken pieces in oil.
Cut onions into chunks; put them, some water and a couple of bouillon cubes in with the chicken.
Cook until tender (2 hours).
Add the celery.
Mix mayonnaise and soy sauce; set aside.
Add the green olives to chicken after 1 1/2 hours.
Mix in sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix oleo, eggs, vanilla, sweetener, applesauce, dates and pecans; set aside.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, cloves and soda.
Add dry ingredients to fruit mixture and mix well.
Bake in angel food cake pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: enterprise plantation's baked turkey and country gravy(serves 20)
directions: Brush a large turkey with vegetable oil or spray with Pam. Season it inside and out with salt and pepper.
Place a peeled onion inside the cavity.
(Reserve the giblets for a later Turkey Gumbo, augmented with smoked turkey necks and canned oysters.)

title: tasty barbecue slaw
directions: Shred or chop cabbage.
Mix brown sugar, vinegar, salt, ketchup and hot sauce thoroughly.
Pour into a pan and heat just until it comes to a boil.
Pour the heated liquid over the cabbage and mix well.
Refrigerate for a few hours or overnight before serving. Makes 5 to 6 cups.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Remove juice from beans and marinate in Sweet-Sour Dressing several hours.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown the meat in a large, heavy skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir.
Cook 5 minutes. Add tomato sauce and can of water. Add paste and can of water.
Add 1 teaspoon cumin seed. Simmer. Add chili powder about 1 hour before done and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer, covered, on stove about 2 hours total.
Remove cover and simmer until desired thickness.

title: german chocolate cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and blend.
Let mixture stand 5 minutes.
Drop teaspoons of mixture in sugar to coat.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry wine cups(a molded fruit salad)
directions: In a saucepan, combine cherry juice and sufficient water to make 1 cup liquid.
Add cinnamon stick and bring to boil.
Pour over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice and cherry wine.
Place in refrigerator and chill until jelly-like consistency.
Remove cinnamon stick and fold in cherries, mandarin oranges and almonds.
Grease 8 (4 ounce) molds or cups.
Serves 8.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Line bottom of greased and floured cake pan with chopped pecans.
Mix cake mix as directions indicate.
Pour over pecans. Mix together the butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Drop this mixture by teaspoonfuls on cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Saute pork chops in skillet until brown.
Arrange in baking dish.
Sprinkle flour, paprika, salt and pepper over chops. Combine soup, water, sour cream, onions and parsley in bowl.
Pour over chops.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until tender. Uncover.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.
Serve with rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Marinate
meat in French dressing for 1 hour, refrigerated. Thread
meat
and
vegetables, alternately, on 4 wooden skewers. Lay
Kabobs
on cooking grill.
Brush with remainder of
French dressing.
Cook
until desired tenderness, turning Kabobs
over halfway during cooking and basting with dressing. Yield:
2 servings (each person has 2 Kabobs).

title: chocolate dream bars
