directions: Combine butter and 1/3 cup brown sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup flour.
Mix well.
Press into the bottom of a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes until lightly brown.
Combine eggs, 1 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup flour, baking powder, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans and chocolate.
Spoon mixture over hot crust.
Bake 20 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars. Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken with orange sauce
directions: You will also need vegetable oil spray.
Do not use vegetable oil spray near an open flame or a heat source.
Read and follow directions on can before using.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon in a bag.
Boil 1 cup sugar and butter in a saucepan.
Open biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Put into bag with sugar and cinnamon and shake.
Put into a Bundt pan and then pour 1/2 of the boiled mixture on it. Then repeat.
Bake at 350° about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: helen's special rice ring
directions: In skillet, cook onions and pepper in oil or margarine until tender.
Add soup and tomato puree.
Season with a little sugar, garlic powder, chili powder and chopped parsley.
Add 1 or 2 cups of meat; put into rice ring.
Cook amount of rice needed.
Can just serve over rice.

title: fruit salad mold
directions: Drain juice from fruit cocktail and cook juice 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in jello and cream cheese (can use mixer to smooth out).
Add fruit cocktail and crushed pineapple; mix well.
Refrigerate about 2 hours until it starts to set.
Whip whipping cream and stir in.
Put into mold and refrigerate until set.
Superb!

title: rice casserole with sour cream cheese and chilies
directions: Place one-third of the cooked rice in a well-greased, ovenproof serving dish of 4-quart capacity.
Spread 1 cup of the sour cream over the rice and sprinkle generously with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with half the chilies, the Monterey Jack cheese and chopped scallions.

Repeat the layers in the same order. Finish with the last third of the rice and the sour cream. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and the rice is heated all the way through.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fish in buttered pan; sprinkle with salt, water and evaporated milk.
Bake at 350° until fish is tender, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Press onto an ungreased glass cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake approximately 12 minutes at 350°.

title: wax beans o'brien
directions: Cook pimiento and onion in butter for 3 minutes.
Add salt and beans and cook 5 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Add water and heat to boiling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and salt.
Beat eggs, add to sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk and flavor.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: fried eggplant rounds
directions: Peel the eggplant, slice thin and sprinkle with salt. Put the slices on a plate, weigh them down with another plate and let drain for 1 1/2 hours. Pour off liquid and pat eggplant dry with paper towels. Dredge in seasoned flour, then saute them in batches in 1/4 inch hot oil until they are golden and crispy on both sides. Transfer with slotted spoon to paper towels to drain and sprinkle with salt. Serve with your favorite spaghetti sauce on the side.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain. Combine seasoning and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Heat to simmering.
Jar and seal.
Be careful to avoid boiling as that makes pickles soft.
To add color, add 1 teaspoon turmeric.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar;
add	well
beaten egg yolks. Sift 3 cups
flour with baking powder.
Add to butter mixture. Add all of	lemon
extract.
In
separate
bowl,
mix pecans, cherries and pineapple.
Sprinkle
cup
flour over and mix together. Beat egg
whites until stiff.
Fold in batter.
Add fruit mixture last.
Spoon
mixture into tube pan.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 250° for 3 hours, then 300° for 1 hour.	Cool thoroughly;
then turn out.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add shallot.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Add tomatoes; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Place tomato mixture in container of electric blender; cover and process until smooth.
Add milk and next 3 ingredients; process 5 seconds.
Return tomato mixture to pan and cook over medium heat 8 minutes or until heated.
Garnish with fresh oregano, if desired.
Yields 4 cups.

title: meatball stew and dumplings
directions: Mix ground beef, onions, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper, Worcestershire sauce, egg and water.
Form into small balls.
Brown in oil.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Remove balls.
Blend in baking mix, salt, pepper and 1/2 tsp. paprika into the fat in skillet.
Stir in 2 cups water.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Add balls, carrots, potatoes, green pepper, celery and onion.
(Add water if needed.)
Mix dumplings according to package (buttermilk baking mix).
Drop by spoonfuls into hot stew.
Cook, uncovered on low for 10 minutes.
Then cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Remove dumplings and stir in 3/4 cup sour cream.

title: ham rolls(good)
directions: Turn rolls out of foil pan.
Rub sides and bottom of pan thinly with margarine.
Melt margarine.
Blend with onion, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed.
Slice open all rolls (do not separate rolls individually before slicing).
Spread mixture over inside top and bottom of rolls.
Place top portion with ham slices.
Place cheese slices on bottom half.
Assemble rolls to make sandwiches.
Press down slightly.
Replace in pan. Bake covered with foil for 10 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes longer.
(Can be frozen before baking, thaw before baking.)

title: red velvet pie
directions: Add thawed raspberries, lemon juice and sugar to boiling water. Refrigerate until partly set. Blend well the cream cheese, vanilla, confectioners sugar, salt and milk.
Whip the cream. Beat cream cheese mixture into whipped cream.
Spread 1/2 cream cheese mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Cover with half of the raspberry mixture, then rest of cheese mixture, then balance of raspberry mixture.
Refrigerate until set, for at least 4 hours.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: charleston french dressing(for fruit salad only)
directions: Mix dry ingredients with 2 tablespoons vinegar with electric mixer.
Add very slowly cold cooking oil and continue beating. Add remaining vinegar.
Chill several hours.
Serve over fruit such as pears, peaches, pineapple, etc.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan with no-stick cooking spray.

In a large bowl, with a mixer at medium speed, beat flour, 1 cup butter (cut into pieces), 1/2 cup of sugar and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Press firmly into pan and bake 20-23 minutes or until golden brown.

title: herb filled spiral bread(2 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Pour hot tap water over butter, sugar and salt in small mixing bowl.
Let cool to 115°. It is not necessary for butter to melt completely.
With plastic blade in place (on food processor), add 3/4 cup warm water, 3 cups flour and yeast mixture to work bowl.
Process for several seconds until mixed.
Remove cover and add butter mixture and 1 cup flour. Process briefly.
Add enough remaining flour, a cup at a time, and process after each addition, until dough is still soft, but not sticky and bounces back when touched.
This kneading process should take no longer than a minute.

title: holiday breakfast
directions: Cook sausage and crumble.
Mix milk, salt, mustard and eggs. Pour over all other ingredients, tossing lightly.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° for a souffle breakfast.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and extracts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Put cake in a cold oven and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: marinated steak
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, honey or brown sugar, vinegar, ginger and garlic.
Marinate 8 hours in this mixture for delicate flavor, overnight for more pronounced flavor.
Poke meat with two prong fork while marinating.
Use sauce to brush on while cooking.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
(Better cooked on grill, but can use broiler.)
Carve diagonally in 1/4 inch strips.

title: slaw
directions: Place cabbage, green pepper and onion in large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar.
In saucepan, combine 1 teaspoon sugar, mustard, celery seed, salt, vinegar and oil.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for 4 hours.

title: cucumber pickle
directions: Cover cucumbers with brine of salt, 2 quarts water and lime. Let stand overnight; drain.
Cover with mixture of remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Pack in hot jars.
Fill jars with hot syrup.
Seal.

title: pecan cobbler
directions: You also need 1 deep 9 x 13-inch disposable pan.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Use a heavy saucepan and melt candy bars in the 2 cups of milk; let cool.
Beat eggs and sugar; add all other ingredients. If needed, you can add more milk.
Put in freezer and let it churn.

title: sawdust pudding
directions: Drain pineapple juice and save.
Add pineapple to jello and stir.
Put miniature marshmallows over top.
Set and let jell. Cook sugar, flour, pineapple juice and egg over low heat until thick.
Let cool.
When good and cool, pour over top of marshmallows.
Whip small package of Dream Whip; stir in small package of cream cheese.
Spoon over second layer.

title: cut-out chocolate cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, blending well. Chill about 1 hour or until firm enough to roll.

title: lemon layered delight
directions: Mix oleo, nuts and flour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: very traditional english scones
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and granulated sugar in large bowl.
Add butter; mix with blender by hand or pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.

title: "legal" catsup(diabetic)
directions: Combine tomato juice and vinegar.
Add sweetener and garlic a little at a time until flavor is just right for you.
Use as a substitute for commerical catsup.

title: enchiladas with cream cheese and mushrooms
directions: Cook onion and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, honey, chili powder, cumin, coriander and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for about 30 minutes, or until thick, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.

title: exquisite cake
directions: Melt the butter and mix with flour and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes and cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into ready made crust.
Top with some chocolate shavings.
Put in refrigerator until cool.

title: easy beef sausage and black bean soup
directions: Saute carrots and celery in a little oil.
Add sausage (cut lengthwise in half, then crosswise into 1/2-inch slices).
Add water and soup to the sauteed vegetables and sausage.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 15 minutes or so, stirring occasionally.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix and bake in three cake pans.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
With electric beater, gradually add sugar, then cream cheese, until blended thoroughly.
Put mixture in pie shell.
Cover with pie filling. Chill several hours.

title: sausage and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender, then drain. Stir in butter. Brown sausage and drain. Add sausage to macaroni. Add pepper and spaghetti sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans on the bottom of a small casserole dish. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco mix together.
Spread over beans.
Cover with olives.
Sprinkle Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese heavily over.
Sprinkle with chopped tomato and onion. Refrigerate.
Should be removed from refrigerator 20 minutes before serving.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour and sweet milk alternately.
Add well beaten egg whites. Fold in baking powder. Pour batter into two 8 or 9-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well and put in loaf pan.
Place in larger pan of water. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: best tartar sauce
directions: Mix together.
Ready to serve over fish.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Whip eggs with fork; set aside.
Mix rest with potatoes; add eggs.
Mix.
Preheat oven to 350°, then cut to 250°.
Put rack on bottom.
Cook until crust is brown.
Move rack up, turn oven to 200° and cook for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip-peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butters, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, salt and soda.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Roll in balls; press down. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted and well blended.
Cook over low heat 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

title: homemade sauerkraut(kapusta kiszona)
directions: Shred cabbage (discard the bright green outer leaves).
Toss with salt, caraway seeds and dill seeds.
Pack mixture into a clean sterilized dry crock.
Press down with wooden spoon or mallet, leaving about 1-inch headspace.
If too much liquid forms, pour it away.
The sauerkraut should remain below a layer of liquid.
Weigh down on cabbage with a sterilized plate with something heavy (like a bowl with a heavy rock inside).
Nothing metallic should come in contact with the kraut.
Check every few days.
Keep in crock until completely fermented.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix by	hand
and
bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain
juice
from peaches, place in a pot.
Add sugar, cinnamon,
nutmeg,
butter, vanilla and salt.
You must have 2 crusts, one for the bottom and one for the top of the cobbler. In a
10 x 13-inch baking pan, place the first crust (which is the bottom crust).
Heat the drained juice, cinnamon, butter, nutmeg, vanilla flavor, sugar and salt until it boils.
Place drained peaches in baking pan.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Spoon 1/2 c. fudge in pie crust. Spread 1/2 of Cool Whip over fudge and place in freezer for 10 minutes. Pour milk in a large bowl. Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Add pudding. Beat 2 minutes until smooth. Stir in remaining Cool Whip. Add to pie crust. Refrigerate for 3 hours. Drizzle with remaining fudge for decoration. Serve.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler; cook on medium heat until thickness of pudding desired. Pour into pie crust. Whip whites. Put meringue on top and brown in oven. Cool and cut.

title: squash and potato casserole
directions: Put a little cooking oil or margarine in a large skillet.
Put squash, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper in skillet.
Put in water to cover; cook slow until done.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Slice chicken into strips.
Marinate in oil and soy sauce for 30 minutes.
While chicken is marinating, bring chicken bouillon to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Clean broccoli, trim stem ends and steam or microwave.
Heat a heavy skillet.
When hot, toast sesame seed until brown, shaking the pan so they don't stick.
Remove seed from pan; reserve.
Add chicken and marinating liquid to the hot pan.
Stir-fry chicken quickly until opaque and juice flows golden (not red).
Sprinkle with garlic powder and toss with lemon juice just before serving. Arrange chicken on platter with rice and broccoli.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and garnish with lemon slices. Serves 3 to 4.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in large saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Pour into a serving bowl.
Serve warm or cold sprinkled with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: flank steak barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients except steak.
Slice flank steak into very thin layers, not strips.
Marinate steak in mixture overnight. Grill meat, turning once.
Grills quickly.

title: rich man's shortbread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add flour.
Press in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Cool completely.

title: coconut chocolate squares
directions: Melt butter in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Put in graham cracker crumbs and pat down on bottom and edge of baking dish. Spread walnuts, chocolate chips and coconut.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder into bowl. Set aside. In another bowl, beat together butter and 3/4 cup sugar until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla until mixture is smooth and light. Add milk alternately with flour to sugar mixture, beating thoroughly. Spread less than half of the batter into a 9 x 1 1/2-inch greased pan. Sprinkle with 1 cup berries. Spoon remaining batter on top, smoothing out carefully. Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup berries and top with 2 tablespoons sugar. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with milk or a dip of vanilla ice cream.

title: party tenderloin sandwiches
directions: Place tenderloins in large pan.
Combine the next 8 ingredients in a small mixing bowl, mixing well.
Makes about 1 cup.
Pour marinade over tenderloins.
Cover tightly with foil; refrigerate overnight, turning meat over several times.

title: holiday snack mix
directions: Dump above ingredients in large pan.
Heat in 250° oven; stirring often.
When cereal mixture is hot (about 1 hour in oven), add seasoning mixture a little at a time.
Stirring well. Heat for 2 hours in 250° oven.
Stir often.
Let cool in oven.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend together the flour, salt and lard or shortening.
Mix together the egg, vinegar and water.
Pour egg and water mixture into flour mixture and stir.
Shape into smooth ball and let stand 20 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes with ginger
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut potatoes crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish; top with raisins, ginger and margarine.
In a saucepan, combine honey, apples or pineapple juice.
Heat over low heat 2 to 3 minutes, stirring to blend well.
Pour honey mixture over potatoes and bake 20 minutes. Spoon liquid over potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: hard candy or glass candy
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard balls in water or brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat. After boiling has ceased, stir in flavoring and coloring.
Pour onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; break into pieces.
Store in tight container.
Will keep up to six months.

title: wild rice and curry chicken
directions: You will need a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking or casserole dish.

title: hamburger hot pot
directions: Fry hamburger and onions together.
Add the next 5 ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Then add the last 5 ingredients and simmer for 1 more hour.

title: fruit juice cooler
directions: Chill all ingredients separately.
Combine all together; mix well.
Pour over ice cubes in serving glasses.
Serve immediately. Yields 4 cups.

title: hawaiian turkey and cheese sandwiches
directions: Preheat broiler.
Combine turkey, olives, mayonnaise and cheese in small bowl.
Place pineapple slices on muffin halves. Spoon turkey mixture over pineapple slices.
Arrange on broiler pan.
Broil about 4 inches from heat until hot and bubbly.
Great for leftover turkey.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper in skillet. Add remaining ingredients and pour into casserole.

title: cherry salad
directions: Beat sugar and cheese together.
Add Cool Whip, Bing cherries (a little juice) and then the rest of the ingredients.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Butter bread on both sides and place in bottom of baking dish. Layer sausage, onion and cheese.
Mix eggs with half and half. Pour over top.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until egg and cheese are done.

title: new orleans shrimp creole
directions: Make a golden brown roux of fat and flour.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Simmer until soft.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer over low heat for about 20 minutes.
Add shrimp, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly until shrimp turns pink. Add parsley, onion tops and additional water, if necessary.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, garlic powder and oregano.
Spread evenly in a quiche pan.
Spread pizza sauce over the top.
Sprinkle pepperoni, green onion and green pepper over sauce.
Cover and place in microwave for 5 minutes on High. Remove and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese.
Place in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, sugar and vinegar together; set in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: toll house chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in Nestle semi-sweet chocolate chips and pecans.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Drain and add vegetables and soup.
Mix well.
Spoon into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until Tater Tots are lightly browned.
Serves 10.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Remove crust from bread and cut up.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place bread on bottom, then put sausage on top of bread.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard; mix well and pour over sausage.
Add cheese, then mushroom soup over all.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade pea salad
directions: Put peas in medium size bowl.
Cut up 2 boiled eggs, pickles, onions and cheese.
Add to peas.
Mix in separate bowl milk, mustard, Miracle Whip salad dressing, paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Whip with hand beater a couple of minutes until slightly thick.
If not thick enough, add more Miracle Whip.
Pour on pea mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Layer 2 sliced boiled eggs on top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Ready to serve.

title: justin's bo-getti
directions: Cook spaghetti or other pasta in boiling water until al dente. Brown sausage until no longer pink (I use link style and cut into small pieces, removing the casings).
Drain fat; put sausage back into pan.
Pour Prego sauce over sausage and simmer 5 minutes. Serve with grated Mozzarella cheese over top.
Round this out with a salad and garlic bread on the side for a great meal.

title: "grandma black's dumplings"
directions: Cut Crisco into flour to which baking powder has been added. Add milk and water.
Makes thick dough.
Roll out fairly thin. Flour top and bottom of dough.
Cut up in small squares and let sit about 30 minutes or longer.
Drop in boiling chicken broth and just cook a minute or so.
Deboned chicken may be added or served separately.

title: crispy baked barbecued chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, brown sugar, chili powder, garlic powder, dry mustard, celery seed and cayenne.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brush with melted butter.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken, skin side down and so pieces don't touch, on a baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture. Bake uncovered in 375° oven about 50 minutes or until tender.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a large skillet or wok, heat oil.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic, stirring frequently.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add broccoli, zucchini and carrots.
Continue stirring and cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Add wine, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix jello according to box directions.
When cool, add cottage cheese and stir.
Add salad dressing and Cool Whip.
Add the remaining ingredients, finely diced, to the jello mixture.
Put in a salad dish and let set.
Serve in salad dish.
All vegetables and fruits should be very finely diced, the smaller the better.

title: tangy dressing
directions: Mix everything, but oil, in a quart jar. Shake until dissolved.
Add oil and shake again.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sugar cookie dough
directions: Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Frost with icing.

title: rice hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Set aside.
In casserole dish, combine butter, English peas, cooked rice, mushroom soup and water.
Add the beef and onion.
Combine all together and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
When it is almost done, sprinkle cheese on top.

title: jam cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, butter, preserves, soda and sugar; mix well.
Stir in buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients. Divide batter evenly among four greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until cakes pull away from sides of pans.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: no-bake apricot coconut balls
directions: In large bowl, combine apricots and coconuts.
Blend well. Shape into small balls.
If desired, roll into powdered sugar.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Melt together mayonnaise and cheese.
Crumble bacon.
Mix 1/2 of bacon with potatoes.
Add cheese mixture; mix.
Spray baking dish with Pam and fill with potatoes.
Sprinkle remaining bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix melted butter and stuffing mix.
Set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1/2 of stuffing mixture gently.
Do not pat down.
Add chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If made ahead and stored in the refrigerator, cook approximately 1/2 hour longer.

title: lindsay's tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out dough; cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 450° until light brown.

title: chicken can can
directions: Put soups and water in saucepan; add rice and chicken.
Bring to full broil.
Cover; let set 5 to 7 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with onion rings.
Bake at 250° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: masterpiece baked beans
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish. Top with bacon.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Place apples in baking dish (9 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle Jell-O over apples.
Combine last 3 ingredients and sprinkle over apples. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: already ready for sloppy joe pizza
directions: Grease a 12-inch pizza pan. Sprinkle bottom with corn meal. Cut butter into flour until mixture is crumbly. Stir 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz and water in.
Mix with fork and form ball.
Press dough over bottom and sides of pan. Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Brown meat. Drain. Add onion and green pepper.

Cook until tender. Stir in remaining cheese spread and barbecue sauce. Stir until cheese is melted. Spoon mixture over crust. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Top with tomato. Continue baking for 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp or crabmeat dip
directions: Blend shrimp or crabmeat with 8 oz. cream cheese, 1/4 cup Catalina Salad dressing, 3 cloves chopped garlic.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Sift flour once and measure.
Add cocoa and 1/2 cup sugar. Sift together 4 times.
Combine egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks, but are still moist and glossy.
Then add rest of sugar by sprinkling about 5 tablespoons at a time over whites and beating until sugar is blended, about 25 strokes each time.
Add flour and sugar mixture, 1/4 at a time, sifting it over whites.
Fold in each addition with flat whip or large spoon.

title: macaroon cherry delight
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip and spread over cooled crust.

title: ground beef and tater tot casserole
directions: Grease a 2 x 9-inch cake pan. Brown the ground beef with the onion, salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Place in pan.
Place the Tater Tots on top of the beef.
Place the soup over the potatoes. Next add the cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. This and a bowl of salad makes a good meal.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown beef and onions; add sauce.
Spread in casserole dish. Cover with sliced cheese.
Spread on sour cream.
Cover with whole roll of crescent rolls.
Mix Parmesan cheese with butter; crumble on top.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 25 minutes.

title: apple strudel
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar.
Work in shortening until it looks like cornmeal.
Add eggs, well beaten, with water and blend well. Let dough set for about 10 minutes.
Shape dough into balls and knead until bubbles form in dough.
Place on small plates and cover.
Let stand about 2 hours.
(I make three rolls from this recipe.
You might try half the recipe the first time and make two rolls to get the feel of pulling the dough.)

title: swiss broccoli soup
directions: Saute 2 tablespoons onion until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until melted.
Can add potatoes and other vegetables if you wish too.

title: little smokies
directions: In a heavy skillet or saucepan dissolve brown sugar in barbecue sauce on low heat.
Add cocktail wieners and cook on medium heat for 25 minutes.
Place in a serving dish and insert toothpicks in each wiener.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots with 1 teaspoon salt until tender.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients thoroughly.
Add carrots and marinate overnight.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Melt margarine.
Add pretzels and sugar.
Press into pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Spread a layer of macaroni in bottom of baking dish.
Spread a layer of cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter. Add enough milk to come up to the top of the macaroni.
Bake at 350°.
If you want a larger amount, double recipe.
Use your imagination.

title: e - z cheese ball
directions: Blend all together. Form a ball and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: heavenly carrots
directions: Place carrots in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in croutons and cheese.
Mix other ingredients and pour over carrot mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: herbal salad dressing
directions: Mix liquid ingredients, then add salt and pepper to taste. Add in sugar and stir.
Add in herbs and mix.
Make any adjustments according to taste.

title: baked stuffed zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini lengthwise.
Parboil 5 to 8 minutes.
Chop onions, peppers and mushrooms.
Saute in skillet with meat.
Add salt and pepper.
Scoop out centers of zucchini.
Chop up centers and combine with meat.
Mix zucchini, centers, meat, stuffing and tomato paste.
Place lengthwise zucchini on a greased pan.
Stuff zucchini.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: blend of the bayou seafood casserole
directions: Use large pan.
Saute in butter the onions, celery, green pepper, garlic and okra for 10 minutes.
Add to this mixture the roux, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add all other ingredients and cook for another hour.
Serve in soup bowl with rice and green onions (chopped).

title: southwest chili
directions: Brown ground turkey; pour into colander and rinse with hot water.
Return turkey to large pot.
Add the rest of ingredients and simmer at medium-high heat for 2 to 3 hours.

title: great-grandmother minnie's rolls
directions: In a bowl, sift the flour. In a separate bowl, dissolve the yeast in 3 tablespoons of warm water. Add the lukewarm water, shortening, sugar and egg. Slowly add the flour, blending well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp and cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together after cream cheese has come to room temperature.
You will need to use a fork to smash the shrimp into the cheese.
After all ingredients are blended, except nuts, form a ball and wrap in aluminum foil.

title: hamburger upside-down pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Saute onion, green pepper and meat until brown.
Add tomato sauce and other ingredients, except biscuits. Heat mixture until bubbling hot.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Top with biscuits.
Bake, uncovered, until biscuits are done.
Remove from oven and let set 3 to 5 minutes.
Cover with serving plate and invert.

title: chilli burro's
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add grated cheese, chilies, sauce and onion. Mix and simmer until cheese is melted.
Spoon into flour tortillas and roll.
Fry in vegetable oil until golden brown. Serve with sour cream or salsa.

title: cream pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt. In a medium bowl, beat butter, vanilla, egg yolks and milk until smooth. Stir into sugar mixture. (Reserve egg whites for meringue.) Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly so it thickens evenly and prevents lumps and scorching. Pour filling into crust. Top with meringue, sealing edges. Brown meringue.

title: rice dish(low calorie)
directions: Saute pepper and onion; add hamburg or ground turkey breast. Add Hunts no salt tomato sauce, 2 cups of instant rice, cooked as on package.
Add 1 package of beef broth, 1/2 teaspoon chili and 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder.
Put in 8 x 8-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Spread top with 4 ounces of Cheddar, grated, or Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in microwave oven 8 minutes or 15 minutes in conventional oven.

title: old-fashioned corn relish
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, hot sauce, celery seed and mustard seed in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill. Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Chop beef, olives, onions and mushrooms.
Blend together all ingredients.
Form into two balls. Can be frozen.

title: sour cream chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix baking mix with water until soft dough forms.
Beat for 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth board.
Knead several times.
Roll dough into rectangle (14 x 10-inch).
Place dough in baking dish so that edges are 1/2 inch up sides.
Mix other ingredients; pour over dough.
Bake until edges are brown and knife inserted comes out clean, about 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and oil together, then add eggs, soda, salt, flour and vanilla.
Pour into rectangular baking pan.
Put into cold oven and turn to 325°.
Bake 1 hour.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Heat crabmeat and juices.
Work in cream cheese; add onions. Serve with potato chips or etc.

title: cream tacos
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Cook 2 hours on low.
Serve over chips of your choice.

title: stuffed mayonnaise chicken
directions: You
will
need
toothpicks
for this
recipe.	Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Debone chicken
thighs.
Place 2 tablespoons prepared stuffing mix in each
chicken thigh (skin side out); hold together with toothpicks.
Place chicken close together in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan (skin	side
up).
Spread mayonnaise	on
top
of
chicken.
Sprinkle
with
pepper
(as desired).
Bake in the oven at 350° for about 1 hour, or until top is browned.
With turkey baster, remove all
oil from pan. Serve warm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Place Cheez Whiz in bottom of casserole, then half of squash and onion mixture.
Add beaten eggs and green chilies, mixed together.
Add balance of squash and onion mix.
Crumble 2 pieces of toast over top of casserole; pour chicken soup over all.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: french bread spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Slice bread lengthwise and butter.
Spread on mixture and heat at 350° for 15 minutes.
Broil a few seconds for crust bread.

title: pork roast with mushroom gravy
directions: Bake roast in 2 cups water 1 hour at 450°. Take from oven and add sweet and Irish potatoes, carrots, salt, pepper and onions. Dilute mushroom soup with 2/3 cup water. Stir well and pour over other ingredients. Sprinkle with parsley flakes. Return to oven and bake 30 minutes.

title: skillet macaroni
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Remove beef from skillet.
Cook onion, green pepper and macaroni in meat fat until macaroni turns yellow.
Return meat to skillet.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings and bring to a boil.
Simmer 25 minutes covered.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Put pineapple and jello into pan and cook until jello dissolves, do not let boil.
After mixture cools add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 12 oblong dish. Refrigerate until sets.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: jamalee's sweet cornbread
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in sugar, eggs and milk.
Stir in dry ingredients just until mixed; batter will be lumpy.
Pour in greased square pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mustard chicken
directions: Dust chicken with flour. Saute chicken in butter and oil in skillet until brown. Transfer to a baking dish and allow to cool slightly. Spread each breast with mustard. Saute onion in remaining fat until golden; add mushrooms and saute until tender. Add parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Blend in cream and stir until heated.
Pour this mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove to serving platter. Stir lemon juice into remaining sauce and serve. Serves 4 to 8.

title: black walnut layer cake
directions: Beat butter, 2 c. powdered sugar and vanilla on low speed; continue on high until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix 2 c.
powdered sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and salt and add, alternately, with milk to butter mixture, beating well with each addition.
Stir in walnuts.
In small bowl beat egg whites on high speed until stiff peaks are formed.
Gently fold into creamed mixture.
Divide into 3 prepared baking pans.
Bake 35 minutes on 350°.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans; cool completely on racks.

title: ruby's icebox fruitcake
directions: Bring milk to boil on low heat; stir constantly.
Melt marshmallows.
Pour in gradually all dry ingredients.
Add applesauce or pineapple sauce if needed to help mix.
Put in 2 small containers.
Pack in really well with rolling pin or in one large container.
Can be frozen, but slice before putting away in freezer.

title: original tom and jerry
directions: Mix all ingredients together but not too well as egg whites will deflate.
Serve in cups (warm or cold).

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine in pan the pineapple and Jell-O.
Heat until Jell-O is dissolved.
Let cool.
Then add cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: almond tea
directions: Steep tea bags in 2 cups boiling water for 10 minutes.
Boil sugar in 4 cups water for 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice and flavorings.
Combine the liquids and heat.
Serve hot or cold. May be kept in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Grind together the first 3 ingredients. Cover with boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes. Pour in 1 cup sugar and 1 cup vinegar. Bring to boil; drain. Then add 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups sugar and salt. Let come to boil. Put in hot sterile jars. Seal.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
In saucepan, heat the milk, soup, Velveeta cheese and water on low. Heat tortillas.
Roll tortillas with meat and cheese.
Lay in baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over top of tortillas.
It should be pretty juicy.
Bake in oven until hot and bubbly.

title: pistacchio(greek spaghetti)
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and add the beaten egg, 1/4 cup milk and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
Brown meat and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in the tomato sauce and spices. Set aside.
Melt butter; add flour and milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add a little to the beaten egg and return to saucepan. Stir in remaining cheese.
Layer 1/2 macaroni in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon meat mixture over; add rest of the macaroni. Top with cream sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: caramel icing
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling.
Boil for approximately 5 minutes.
Spread on cake.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: In the basket of the coffeepot, place 1 teaspoon ground nutmeg, 1 tablespoon whole cloves, 1 tablespoon whole allspice and 2 cinnamon sticks.
Plug in coffee maker and perk.
Serve in a mug with a cinnamon stick stirrer.

title: molasses popcorn balls
directions: Combine molasses, corn syrup & vinegar in sauce pan.
Cook stirring occasionally to 240 degrees.
Then continue cooking, stirring constantly to 270 degrees.
When done, add butter and stir only enough to mix.
Sprinkle the salt over the corn in a large bowl.
Then slowly pour the syrup over it, mixing well. Quickly shape into balls using as little pressure as possible.

title: green giant casserole
directions: Drain corn and beans.
Mix corn, beans, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add crackers to cover top and pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together into a mixing bowl, flour, baking powder, sugar, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add to flour mixture.
Then add buttermilk.
Work together with a large wooden spoon until flour is moistened.
Cover bowl.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Roll out the amount to be used on a floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out and put on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(I cover with a clean dish towel.)
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
This dough will keep for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(Fish makes batter thin.)

title: hoppin john
directions: Combine peas and rice in saucepan with enough water or stock to cover. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Put in refrigerator and let cool.
Add other ingredients and mix. Put back in refrigerator to congeal.

title: baker's style chocolate frosting
directions: Cream Crisco and chocolate in medium size bowl.
Gradually mix half the sugar, beating well.
Add milk, egg and remaining sugar, slowly beating until nice and creamy.
Add vanilla; mix.
Spread. Delicious!

title: deer burger steak
directions: Mix meat with dry soup mix.
Shape meat into patties and roll in flour.
Brown in skillet.
Place meat in a baking dish and pour gravy and mushrooms over meat.
Bake 30 minutes at 375° or microwave for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves approximately 4.

title: marinade for beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over beef and marinate for 24 hours.

title: chocolate-banana shortcake
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
In
a
large
mixer
bowl, blend all ingredients, except whipped
cream
and
banana,
on low speed 1/2 minute, scraping bowl
frequently.
Beat
on
medium speed 4 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick
inserted in	center	comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes. Cut	4
servings from
cake.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream and banana slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate.
Excellent with your favorite raw vegetables.

title: party-size quiche lorraine
directions: Make pie crust according to package directions and line a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Fry and crumble bacon.
Grate cheese. Distribute bacon and cheese evenly over crust.
Slightly beat eggs and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over cheese and bacon. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and 300° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
(I also add mushrooms.)

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a large bowl.
Combine butter and cheese in saucepan over low heat until melted.
Blend in sour cream and onions.
Fold into potatoes.
Place into casserole dish; dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake as directed; let cool completely.
Crush Butterfingers.
Mix together beaten egg whites, margarine and powdered sugar; fold in Cool Whip.
Crumble cake.
Layer ingredients in pan, beginning with crushed Butterfingers, cake, then mixture.

title: ham and cheese chicken rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Flatten chicken to even thickness.
Place 1 ham and 1 cheese slice on each breast half. Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Mix soup and milk in baking dish.
Place chicken roll-ups in mixture and spoon to cover each. Cover dish and bake 1 hour.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, put layer of chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Top with crumbs, mixed with poppy seed.
Pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can make a day ahead.

title: barbecues
directions: Mix all this together in heavy bottom kettle (or crock-pot). Cook slow (if not in crock-pot, stir often so it won't burn).
This makes a great sandwich with fresh coleslaw.
Also freezes real well.
Approximate (regular) cooking time:
2 hours.
(Slow cooker.)

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add peppermint oil and food coloring.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar. Chill 1 to 2 hours or until firm.
(Mints can be pressed into candy molds before chilling, if desired.)
Mints may be frozen in an airtight container up to 2 months.

title: salted pecans
directions: Sprinkle pecans with butter. Then salt. Mix well and spread in a shallow pan. Bake in hot oven 10 minutes, stirring often. Drain on absorbent paper towel.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Stir molasses, sugar and vinegar together.
Boil slowly.
Add butter and vanilla, when drop forms hard ball in cold water.
Pour mixture over bowl of popped corn and stir fast.
When nearly cool, butter hands and form into balls.

title: ayers barbecue for sandwiches
directions: Brown meat in shortening until crumbly.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into browned meat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Watch carefully to prevent burning.
Serve on a toasted bun.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour a little of the batter in a pan.
Add some of the apple mixture.
Repeat until all is used up, ending with batter on top.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: berliners
directions: Mash yolks of hard-boiled eggs until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll in small strips the size of small finger and 5 inches long.
Make into a figure 8 and top with whipped egg white before baking.
Bake in 375° oven for about 8 minutes.
Watch closely as they burn easily.

title: the best brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edge of pan. Cool in pan.
Yields approximately 16 brownies.

title: neptune pie
directions: Combine crabmeat, onion, cheese, peas, salt and pepper.
Put in greased casserole.
Mix Bisquick, eggs and milk.
Pour over mixture. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Casserole is done when knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: fried pork and beans
directions: Brown onion in 2 tablespoons Crisco oil.
Add beans.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Pour over gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise, blending well.
Gradually add Jell-O, mixing until well blended. Stir in pineapple; chill until slightly thick.
Fold in whipping cream.
Pour into glass oblong dish (13 x 9 1/2-inch) or 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix flour, butter and sour cream.
Divide into 4 parts.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill.
Roll out dough on 12 x 6-inch pan (greased).
Place 1 cup cheese on each flattened dough.
Also add 1/4 cup seasoned salt and roll up.
Seal ends, fix tears, slit each roll across top of each loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crustless potato quiche
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and stir well.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until set.
Sprinkle bacon evenly on top; bake an additional 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan.
Stir in flour, being sure to smash lumps.
Stir in juice from can of pineapple.
Bring to a boil and stir until thickened.

title: joe's breakfast pizza
directions: Break up bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Add cheese.
Add egg and milk mixture.
Filling of your choice. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange velvet pie
directions: Prepare 1 baked 9-inch pie shell as directed.
While shell bakes, squeeze fruit juices.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
With electric mixer, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in sugar, orange and lemon juices, then gradually beat in the gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate until almost set.
With electric mixer, whip cream; quickly beat into gelatin mixture.
Turn into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until set.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onions in oil. Add tomatoes, chili sauce and seasoning.
Simmer for 35 minutes; add shrimp and cook for 10 minutes longer. Serve over rice.

title: butter fudge bars
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and 2 squares chocolate together.
Add the eggs, sugar and flour.
Put into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Brown 1/4 cup butter slightly.
Add powdered sugar, cream and vanilla.
Put topping on the warm brownies.
Melt the remaining butter and chocolate.
Ice brownies with this mixture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, blending thoroughly. Stir in nuts.

title: broccoli-chicken quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Preheat cookie sheet for 5 minutes. Place pie crust on preheated cookie sheet for 6 minutes.
Remove pie crust.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Mix broccoli, chicken and cheese together.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, milk and seasonings together.
Pour mixture over broccoli, chicken and cheese.
Spoon the mixture into crust.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chinese marinated vegetables
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper together and let stand.

title: homemade spaghetti
directions: Put spaghetti on to boil.
Brown ground meat; drain and add onions, seasons and tomato sauce.
When spaghetti is ready, drain and add meat sauce and mix together.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Slice crosswise or lengthwise in 1/4-inch slices.
Peel and slice onions.
On a piece of foil, alternate slices of potato and onion.
Pour Italian dressing over and close foil securely.
Cook on a hot grill, turning once in about 30 minutes.
Check for tenderness.
May be cooked in the microwave in a covered dish instead of foil.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage about 1/2 inch thick.
Brown in oil.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and basil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes and liquid, bouillon, cabbage and pepper.
Bring soup to boil. Reduce heat and simmer covered 1 hour.
Add beans with liquid, cook another 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Into a greased and floured pan put coconut and nuts.
Follow directions on cake mix and pour over coconut and nuts mixture. Microwave butter and cream cheese.
Mix with powdered sugar. Place spoonfuls of this mixture all over the top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy dessert
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add the eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add the almond extract.
Stir in the flour and baking powder; mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Put mixture into pan.
Spoon the pie filling into the cake in 16 spots.

title: jewish crumb cake
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, cinnamon, nuts and coconut to make crumbs; set aside.
Beat butter or oil with sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add salt and eggs; beat at high speed.
Sift flour with soda; add to beaten mixture alternately with sour cream.
Pour half of batter into greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle the crumbs over it.
Cut through batter with knife.
Add remaining batter; top with rest of crumbs. Cut through batter with knife several times.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 50 minutes.
Let sit 10 to 15 minutes, then turn out. This can also be baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: Mix enchilada mix and tomato sauce.
Coat chicken in mixture and place in crock-pot.
Cover chicken with leftover mix.
Cook on high 1 hour or low 4 to 5 hours.
Remove chicken.
Stir in cheese and sour cream.
Return chicken.
Cook on low 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve.

title: mini-cheese ball
directions: Beat
cream
cheese with mixer.
Add steak sauce, onion and then
Cheddar cheese and beat thoroughly.
Shape into log or ball. Roll in parsley, nuts or paprika.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Simmer tomato sauce with seasonings; in separate frying pan, saute hamburger and onions until meat is brown.
Add tomato sauce and simmer for 15 minutes.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with half the zucchini slices.
Cover with half of meat mixture. Spoon on half of sour cream and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with olives.
Repeat layering process with remaining half portion.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes; remove foil (save) and bake for 10 minutes more to brown cheese.
Remove from oven, re-cover with foil and allow to stand for 15 minutes until layers are set.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine; add water and potatoes.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and add cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add milk, slowly, until you have reached desired consistency.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Place bread crumbs in buttered baking dish.
Set aside.
Scald milk and butter.
In large bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, cinnamon, raisins and salt.
Combine with milk and butter.
Stir well and pour over crumbs in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out without any mixture on it.

title: low-fat frozen strawberry pie
directions: You can substitute any kind of fruit.
I've used pineapple and mangos.

title: little fruit cake balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Shape into bite-size pieces and cook 10 to 15 minutes at 325° on cookie sheet, until light brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Drain crushed pineapple and spread on top of cooled pudding.
Slice bananas over pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and decorate with maraschino cherry halves.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: mini sausage quiches
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese in medium bowl until creamy. Blend in flour; refrigerate 1 hour. Roll into 24 (1 inch) balls; press each into mini muffin cup. Preheat oven to 375°. To prepare filling, crumble sausage into small skillet. Cook over medium heat until browned, stirring occasionally. Drain off any drippings. Sprinkle evenly into pastry shells in muffin cups; sprinkle with Swiss cheese and chives. Whisk eggs, half and half, salt and cayenne until blended; pour over sausage in pastry shells. Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until set. Remove from pans. Serve hot. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add next four ingredients.
Line 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with chips.
Spread meat mixture over chips.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hash browns for 25
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine all ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Mix well and pour into large, oiled baking pan, about 10 x 15-inch.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for about 2 hours.

title: creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool cake 15 minutes.
Use a fork to poke holes in top of cake.

title: clam dip
directions: Put cream cheese at room temperature a few hours before mixing to soften.
Mix cream cheese with clam juice, pouring clam juice in cream cheese as needed to make cream cheese creamy.
Mix cream cheese with mixer until smooth.
Add all of the other ingredients. Can be made the night before.
Serve with favorite chips.

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak beans overnight with Adolph's meat tenderizer.
Cook slowly for about an hour, then add other ingredients and cook until beans are done.

title: millionaire fruit pie
directions: Cook cherries, pineapple, sugar and cornstarch until thick. Add cherry jello; cool.
Add bananas, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells and let set.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: honey 'n' spice chicken bake
directions: Brush chicken with butter; season with salt and pepper.
Place chicken skin side down on rack on broiler pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Combine 57 sauce and honey.
Remove chicken from oven.
Turn skin side up.
Brush with half of the 57 sauce and honey mixture.
Continue to bake chicken 15 to 20 minutes longer or until tender.
Brush with remaining sauce.

title: cherry cake
directions: Sift together first four ingredients.
Add next four ingredients and beat two minutes.
Add eggs. Beat two more minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° in two 9-inch layer pans.

title: upside-down cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
To top, add 2 cups canned fruit (peaches are very good); add 2 cups fruit juice with 1/2 cup sugar added.
When done, fruit will be on bottom, batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peak-a-boo cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt into bowl.
Add brown sugar, shortening (softened) and water.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Fold in oats.
Sprinkle a board with powdered sugar. Roll dough very thin.
Cut with cutter.
Cut a design in half with hole in it.
Place cookies on baking sheet.
Top with jelly and cover with a cookie that has a hole in it on top of jelly, lightly pressing edges together.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Bring butter, Coke and cocoa to a boil.
Pour over flour, sugar and salt; mix well.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Take out of mixer and add marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: philadelphia clam chowder, 1902
directions: Put bacon into the bottom of a good-sized saucepan.
Pare and cut potatoes; dice.
Chop the clams and roll the crackers.

Put a layer of potatoes on top of bacon, then onion, thyme, marjoram, parsley, salt and tomatoes (chopped); then a layer of chopped clams and continue alternating until all ingredients have been used.
Add the stock; cover and place over a very low flame. Simmer for half hour without stirring.

title: potato salad
directions: Gradually add all of the ingredients in a large bowl, thoroughly mixing each item with a fork or spoon.
After all ingredients are mixed, add salad dressing, mayonnaise or your favorite dressing.
Season to taste and serve with your favorite meat or poultry.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Brown meat; may add bacon bits.
Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
This can be frozen before being baked. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow extra time if frozen.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easter resurrection rolls
directions: Give each child a triangle of crescent rolls.
The crescent roll represents the cloth that Jesus was wrapped in.
Give each child a marshmallow.
This represents Jesus and his purity.
Have them dip the marshmallow in melted butter.
This represents the oils of embalming.
Then dip the buttered marshmallows in the cinnamon and sugar.

This represents the spices used to anoint the body. Then wrap up the coated marshmallow tightly in the crescent roll (not like a typical crescent roll, but bring the sides up and seal the marshmallow inside).
This represents the wrapping of Jesus's body after death.
Place in 350 degree oven for 10-12 minutes.
The oven represents the tombs (pretend like it was 3 days later.)
When the rolls have cooled slightly, open rolls and discover that Jesus is no longer there.
HE IS RISEN!!
The marshmallow melts and the crescent roll is puffed up but empty.

title: large cranberry salad
directions: Soften unflavored gelatin in a small amount of water. Dissolve all gelatin in boiling water.
Add sugar, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm in mold.

title: tangy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and the herb-spice mix.
Gradually add broth and milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken, mushrooms and pimento. Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Prepare spaghetti as directed on package.
Add eggs and the grated Parmesan cheese (included in spaghetti dinner package).
Layer spaghetti mixture, chicken mixture and cheese in 9-inch dish.
Make 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: coconut cake-cocoa lopez
directions: Bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is hot, punch holes all over top.
Mix Coco Lopez and Eagle Brand milk together and pour over hot cake and let cake cool.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top.
Keep in refrigerator or freezer.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Serve with cornbread. Freezes well.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, veal and pork, day old bread, grated cheese and egg; shape into meatballs.
Brown onions and clove of garlic in olive oil; remove garlic when brown.
When partially cooked pour can of plum tomatoes into meatballs, cook down and add water as needed.
After an hour of cooking, add 1 can of tomato paste.
Complete cooking in about 2 hours.
Boil water, add spaghetti and 1 tablespoon salt.
Keep stirring macaroni until tender or al dente.
Pour sauce over spaghetti.
One loaf of garlic bread and a salad and you have a meal!

title: sugar cookies for centerpieces
directions: You will need large cookie cutters (any shape), thin wooden dowels and colored milk or decorator frosting.

title: homemade eggnog pie
directions: In a small bowl soften gelatin, and water, set aside.
In a saucepan combine sugar
and corn starch, gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and pour in mixture.
Bake at 400° for ten minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in order given and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn flake crunch
directions: Bring Karo syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until peanut butter has melted and is creamy. Pour mixture over corn flakes.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: orange julius
directions: Put orange juice in blender.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover blender and blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix cooked broccoli with mushroom soup and Velveeta.
Pour in casserole and top with buttered, unseasoned croutons.
Warm thoroughly in 350° oven.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixture. Sift baking powder, flour and pinch of salt together.
Add milk and flour alternately to mixture, a little of each at a time.
Flour nuts lightly and add to mixture.
Beat egg whites separately and fold in carefully (do not beat).
Bake at 350° to 375° (start at 375° and turn down to 350°, 40 to 50 minutes).
Use a good sized pan.

title: sauerkraut and chops
directions: Brown pork chops in nonstick pan.
Place half of onion rings, garlic flakes, sauerkraut, apple juice, caraway seed, salt, thyme and pepper in slow cooker.
Add pork chops.
Place remaining half of ingredients on top of chops.
Cover and cook for 6 to 8 hours. Can be cooked on stove for 4 hours.

title: kids' favorite sandwiches
directions: Mix together and put in hot dog rolls.
Wrap in foil and bake until cheese melts.
Makes about 12.

title: sausage-lentil soup
directions: Cook sausage in 1 cup water, breaking up as it cooks.
Drain. Add broth, water, lentils, tomatoes, onions and garlic.
Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally, until lentils are almost tender. Stir in pasta.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes until lentils and pasta are tender.
Stir in spinach and cook 2 to 3 minutes longer, until tender.
Serve hot sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: baked squash
directions: Mash squash; add onion, 1/2 of bread crumbs, salt, pepper, sugar, eggs and 1/2 of oleo.
Combine well.
Pour squash into baking dish; melt remaining oleo and spread on top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix prepared mustard and currant jelly in chafing dish or saucepan on low heat.
Slice wieners, diagonally, in bite-size pieces.
Add to sauce and heat through.
Serve hot.

title: mississippi river catfish gumbo(serves 4 to 6)
directions: This recipe originally came from Southern Living magazine. It makes a great Christmas happy for friends and teachers.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Put ingredients into blender; blend until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch granola or graham cracker crust.
Freeze.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, brown sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in raisins and caraway seed. Add buttermilk; stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn batter into a greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan.
With floured fingers, pat dough evenly into pan and brush top with a little melted butter or margarine.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool bread before removing from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.
Serve warm or cold with butter and jam.
Very good.

title: squash puppies
directions: Combine meal and flour.
Add onions and squash.
Stir in egg and milk to make a stiff batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil until brown on all sides.
Makes 24.

title: holiday nuggets
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cream together shortening, butter and powdered sugar.
Blend together vanilla, almond and nuts.
Then mix all of the ingredients together and make balls the size of walnuts and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crazy pie
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients.
Add crackers and boil hard for 2 minutes.
Do not stir.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and then flour and soda.
Crush bananas and mix in.
Add nutmeats.
Place in greased loaf bread pan and bake in moderately hot oven (350°) for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking soda in bowl and set aside. Combine both sugars, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add eggs. Add dry ingredients to the moist ingredients and mix well.
Last, add chocolate chips.
Put dough in fridge to get cold, then preheat oven to 375°.
Place dropped cookie dough by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
In large bowl, cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, water and pumpkin.
Blend in flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Can stir in nuts and raisins (optional).
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake about 70 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Measure dry ingredients and sift.
Add alternately with buttermilk, starting and ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Bake in layers at 350° until top is slightly browned.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Simmer for several hours.

title: crunchy potato wedges
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into quarters or chunks.
Combine butter and garlic; mix well.
Dip potatoes into melted butter, then crumbs, coating well.
Salt to taste.
Place on lightly oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done, pouring leftover butter over the potatoes from time to time. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: taco crescents
directions: Brown beef, stirring to crumble; drain excess fat.
Stir in taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Add cheese.
Separate roll dough into triangles.
Place rounded tablespoons of beef mixture on each, roll up and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: forget-me-nots(mini pecan pies)
directions: Mix all together with fork or fingers.
It will seem very crumbly for a while, but keep squeezing flour and oleo/cream cheese together until like pie dough.
Roll into 24 balls and shape in tea pans (2) like mini pie crusts.
Place a few chopped pecans into each cup.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix with fork, cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press in greased pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Beat sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs for 5 minutes and pour over other mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook in double boiler the first 4 ingredients.
When heated well add gradually the egg yolks and cook until custard stage. Then add vanilla.
Layer slices of bananas and layer vanilla wafers and then custard.
Repeat until all custard to used.

title: mocha macaroon pie
directions: Mix sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix egg whites until soft peaks form.

Begin adding sugar mix gradually to egg whites as they beat; beat for 1 to 2 minutes after all sugar is added. Carefully fold in crumbs, nuts, chocolate and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spoon into buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool completely.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature before starting cake.

title: spinach cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease mini muffin pans.
In large skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add spinach, mushrooms, bread crumbs, cheese, yogurt, salt and pepper.
Add crumbled bacon; blend all well.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits. Separate each into 2 layers.
Place a layer in muffin tin, pressing to fill cup.
Fill with spinach mixture.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until brown.

title: pumpkin breaddiagonal, iowa
directions: Mix in order given.
Fill loaf pans 1/2 full.
Makes 3 loaves. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork tenderloins
directions: In skillet, brown chops in a little oleo or pork drippings. Combine cream of mushroom soup, mushroom pieces, beer and onion soup mix.
Place chops in casserole and pour gravy mixture over chops.
Bake 1 hour or more in a 350° oven.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in oblong cake pan.
While hot, punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour condensed milk evenly over cake. When cool, top with topping, then coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Add pineapple to softened cream cheese.
Mix green peppers, salt and onion together.
Add to mixture, then add 1/2 to 1 cup nuts.
Shape into two balls.
Use remaining nuts around the balls. Freeze well.

title: strawberry slushes
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a blender; cover and blend until smooth.
Serve at once before it melts.
You can also use frozen blueberries, raspberries, orange juice or about any other frozen fruit or juice.

title: venison or beef roll
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate. Each day for 3 days, remove from refrigerator and mix well for 5 minutes.
On the fourth day, divide mixture into three (3) parts. Roll each out to resemble a roll of hard salami (roll on hard surface).
Bake at 160° on a wire rack in a shallow pan for 9 hours (turn after 4 1/2 hours).
Remove from oven and roll in a paper towel to remove excess fat.
Cool, slice and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; drain and squeeze.
Mix all ingredients.
Scoop out center of round loaf of pumpernickel or rye bread.
Spoon dip into center of bread.
Use extra bread for dipping.
Also good for dipping vegetables and crackers.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and shortening, adding well beaten eggs.
Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake in oven at temperature of 375° to 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix and bake at 300° until firm.

title: baked chicken sandwich
directions: Cut buns open and butter them.
Spread with filling which has been thoroughly blended.
Roll in aluminum foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fried turkey
directions: Mix crab oil and dressing.
Inject turkey and marinate overnight.
Drain excess marinade.
Bring peanut oil to 350° (I use fish fryer).
Drop whole turkey in oil for 4 minutes per pound.
Make sure oil stays at 350°.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place in layers in greased 2-quart casserole.
Garnish with green pepper slices.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together and cook until clear.
Into cooled crust, arrange strawberries.
Top with cooled Jell-O mixture.
Top with Cool Whip (optional).

title: chicken parm
directions: Roll chicken breasts in bread crumbs seasoned with basil, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Place chicken in baking dish; pat with margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Pour heated spaghetti sauce over chicken and top with grated Mozzarella. Bake uncovered for another 10 minutes.
Serve chicken with sauce over choice of pasta.
Serves 2 and takes 35 minutes to make!

title: brownies
directions: Cream first three ingredients; then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cook at 325° to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool. Cut in squares and remove from pan.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cream eggs and sugar together, then add milk, water, vanilla and Amaretto.
In a 9 x 13 inch pan, melt butter.
While butter is melting, break bread and soak in mixture.
After soaking, pour this mixture into the melted butter.
Put the pan on a cookie sheet and fill it with hot water.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: boiled corn-on-the-cob
directions: Place corn in a large saucepan and cover with water. Add butter, milk and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and boil 12 to 15 minutes. Turn down to simmer until ready to serve.
Remove. Drain.
Salt to taste and serve with additional butter.

title: southern pork chops
directions: Brown chops in a little oil or margarine.
Remove from skillet and render the cut off fat or use oil to make gravy with flour and broth (may be part water).
Season with salt and pepper.
Add sage, brown sugar and vinegar to taste.
Place chops in a shallow baking pan.
Top with onion slice and apple half which has been cored. Stuff cores with raisins and scatter some about.
Pour gravy over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Add liquid, if necessary, and bake for 45 minutes more, covered.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Cut all vegetables into small pieces.
Mix the sauerkraut and vegetables together.
Mix the sugar, vinegar, oil and salt together.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables; let set overnight.
Enjoy!!

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter together. Add egg, vanilla, flour and baking soda to mixture. Make 40 balls and put them in mini cup pans. Bake at 350 degrees. 8 - 10 minutes until lightly golden brown. Do not over bake. They will appear done. Immediately upon removing from oven, press peanut butter cup in center of each cookie.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, flour and jello.
Add eggs, 3/4 cup strawberries (reserve rest for icing), oil and water.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: kentucky hamburgers
directions: Shape beef into 4 to 6 hamburgers.
Wrap with strip of bacon; fasten with toothpick.
Grill or broil.
A 5-star treat!

title: fudge sauce
directions: Melt the chocolate chips and butter over low heat.
Add the evaporated milk and powdered sugar.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla.

title: moonies
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar together; add vanilla.
Mix in flour and pecans or walnuts.
Roll and shape into crescents; place on a cookie sheet.
Bake until golden in a 350° oven.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: elaine's old fashion tea cakes
directions: In a super large mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar and eggs. Alternate adding milk and dry ingredients until all are added. Mix with hands until batter does not stick to your hands (more flour may be added until desired consistency is achieved).
Roll into 1/2-inch sheet and cut cookies.
Place onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until browning on bottom.
Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: bread pudding
