directions: Place bread crumbs in large bowl.
In medium saucepan, scald milk and butter.
Mix sugar, eggs, salt and cinnamon together. Add mixture to scalded milk and butter.
Mix slightly, then add to bread crumbs and mix.
Add raisins and mix.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Place bread pan inside a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan that has about 1-inch of water in it.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (until knife comes out clean).

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Clean and cook whole head of cauliflower until tender-crisp (12 to 15 minutes).
Drain.
Place cauliflower in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly and press evenly on cauliflower.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, until cauliflower is tender and crumb mixture is brown (15 minutes). Yields 6 servings.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Beat eggs, butter, flour, garlic salt and olives.
Blend in cottage cheese and Swiss cheese.
Bake at 375°
for 40 to 45 minutes until center is firm in 9-inch pie pan.

title: kraut conquers all chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and kraut.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture alternately with water, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Pour batter into two well-greased and floured 8-inch round or square pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Fill and frost with Chocolate Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: italian wedding cookies(makes 200 cookies)
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients.
Bake peanuts at 400° until brown. Chop real small and add to the batter.
Add flour, mix well and roll into long pretzel stick shapes.
Cut into diamond shapes. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and drop into icing.
Stir until well coated.

title: amish dressing
directions: In a large bowl, combine bread cubes, potatoes, carrots, celery and parsley.
Add beaten eggs and chicken stock.
Fold in diced chicken.
Mix all ingredients until blended.
Bake at 350° in a well buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes until firm.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: fudge
directions: Cook milk, sugar and margarine in pan for 8 minutes; do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and chocolate chips (nuts if desired).
Mix well. Pour onto large pan.
Allow to cool.
Yields approximately 5 pounds.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Makes 2 Bundt cakes.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: ani's blackberry dumplings
directions: Combine
first
four
ingredients in pan and let stand. Sift dry
ingredients
in
a bowl, add egg and enough milk to make
a stiff batter.
Place first mixture on stove and bring to
a
boil. Drop
dumpling
batter
by teaspoonfuls into hot sauce, reduce heat
and
cover with a lid.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can
be served with cream, ice cream, whipped cream or yogurt.

title: easy overnight salad
directions: Prepare pudding with milk, add marshmallows, whipped cream and oranges. Refrigerate over night. Just before serving add sliced bananas and pineapple.

title: herbed beef
directions: Serves 2 to 4.

title: scrabble(sweet snack)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, then pour melted chocolate over the top.
Mix well.
Pour onto 2 cookie sheets lined with waxed paper.
When cool, break into pieces.
Makes a lot!
Great for gift bags.
Keep in a cool place as it gets sticky if it gets warm.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour steak and brown quickly in skillet with oil.
Remove from skillet and place in crock-pot.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Cook on low (6 to 8 hours) or until steak is tender.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.
Thicken sauce with flour and water mixture.

title: concentrated berry pie
directions: Add juice to instant pie filling.
Beat slowly with hand mixer until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into baked pie crust. Top with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Take large casserole deep dish.
Layer in order: shredded lettuce, tomato, mushrooms, onions, peas, cheese and mayonnaise, then garnish with onion.
Cool in refrigerator before serving.

title: muffin mix
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator in covered container. Bake in muffin tin or pie pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Will store up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: filling for fruit salad, banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour together. Separate eggs (saving whites for meringue if making pudding or pie). Mix sugar and flour mixture together with egg yolks. Add milk and heat on medium heat until slightly thick, stirring often. Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring. If used as a fruit salad filling, add 3 tablespoons peanut butter into filling. Pour mixture over sliced apples, bananas and chopped nuts.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together; drain.
Combine soup, taco sauce, tomatoes and milk and warm.
Layer nachos, meat, cheese and sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal drops
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Cook and stir until thick enough to drop on waxed paper.

title: beef burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter or margarine.
Mix well.
Shape into 8 large patties.
Brush with melted butter or margarine and broil slowly until brown on both sides, turning once.
Cook to desired degree of doneness, 10 to 20 minutes.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into sifted dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Mix well.
Bake on greased sheet at 450°.
Can be stored in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: easy egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add water and vanilla.
Pour into a deep dish pie shell.
Sprinkle with a pinch of nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Place melted shortening and milk in dry ingredients and mix well.
Pat out on floured board.
Cut; place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 biscuits.

title: mom's chicken(a baker family favorite...very quick)
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice, soy sauce, garlic salt and parsley to taste.
Put in oven at 350°, covered.
Baste after 30 minutes.
Cook another 30 minutes.
Remove cover and broil for a few minutes.
May be served in a traditional manner with brown rice and broccoli.
Chicken may be skinned to cut calories.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream the butter with the sugar.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Dissolve 1 teaspoon soda in 2 cups of buttermilk. Alternate additions of 5 cups sifted flour with buttermilk.
One teaspoon of vanilla or lemon extract may be added to enhance flavor.
Bake in a well-greased tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oklahoma cookies
directions: Mix evaporated milk, margarine, sugar, salt and cocoa in medium saucepan; bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Allow to cool for about 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup peanut butter and 3 cups oatmeal. Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Allow to harden.

title: chicken noodle
directions: Cook chicken broth and noodles until tender. Add diced chicken. Season to taste.

title: japanese salad
directions: Mix lettuce, green onions, poppy seed and almonds; refrigerate overnight.
Mix sugar, vinegar, black pepper, oil and salt.
Just before serving, add noodles to salad; pour on dressing and toss.
Serve and enjoy!

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain fat.
Leave to cool.
In separate boiler, add mustard, ketchup, brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Add sausage and simmer 10 minutes. Works well as appetizer with cheese and crackers.

title: baked brown rice
directions: Brown the rice.
Add mushrooms and liquid which you have brought to a boil.
Bake in a
covered casserole in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Do not salt. Serves 6.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook together and cool the egg, flour, sugar and pineapple juice.
Drain pineapple.
Add diced cheese and marshmallows.
Add pineapple mixture to sauce.
Chill for an hour or so.
Before serving, add whipped cream and garnish with nuts.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and cut into halves.
Empty potato centers into bowl and put shells to the side.
Mix the potato centers as you would mashed potatoes with milk and butter.
After getting the consistency you want, add egg and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix well. Spoon mixture back into potato shells.
Top with more cheese, bacon bits and chives.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Combine bread crumbs (reserve 1/4 cup crumbs) with water, mix to a paste and press into bottom of a pie plate or quiche dish. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes to make crust; cool.

title: harvest chutney
directions: In a 5-quart kettle or Dutch oven, combine sugar, vinegar, salt, ground ginger, mustard seed, peppercorns and cayenne.
Bring to boiling.
Mix in tomatoes, apples, zucchini and onions.
Boil gently, uncovered, stirring frequently until almost thickened, about 1 hour.
Add raisins and candied ginger.
Continue cooking, boiling gently uncovered, stirring often until thickened, 10 to 15 minutes.
Fill hot clean canning jars to within 1/4-inch of rims with boiling hot chutney.
Run a spatula down edges between chutney and jars to release air bubbles.
Wipe rims and place scalded lids on top.
Screw on bands.
Place jars on a rack in a canning kettle half full of hot water to cover jars by 1-inch.
Bring to a gentle boil and process 5 minutes.
Remove from water and cool thoroughly.

title: sister v's punch
directions: Pour the ginger ale into a large punch bowl, filling to slightly more than half full.
Empty one container of the frozen sherbet into the punch bowl.
Stir well.
The sherbet will melt and form the rich, foamy frappe.
Add the second container of sherbet and it will keep the punch cold.
Replenish ginger ale as needed.
Add more sherbet as needed.
Serves 30 to 40 people, using punch cups or Dixie cups.
Great anytime.
Kids and adults love it!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add all other ingredients.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and brown.

title: fudge
directions: Place chocolate and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Cook and stir over very low heat until blended.
Add sugar and salt; stir over medium heat and heat to a boil.
Continue boiling, without stirring, until a little forms
a soft ball in cold water (or to 234°).
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; cool to lukewarm (110°).
Then beat until mixture holds its shape.
Pour at once into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cut when cold.

title: linguica in a blanket
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each triangle lengthwise into thirds.
Place linguica on shortest side of each triangle.
Roll up, starting at shortest side and rolling to opposite point.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: hawaiian coconut pudding cake
directions: Mix cake batter according to directions on box.
Pour into two greased 13 x 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.
Cool completely.
In a large mixing bowl, combine pudding mixes, milk and coconut extract.
Beat 2 minutes; add cream cheese and beat well.
Stir in pineapple.
Spread over cooled cakes.
Top with whipped cream; sprinkle with coconut.
Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: hearty bean chili
directions: In a large pan, saute onion and garlic in oil for 1 minute. Stir in beef and cook until well done.
Stir in beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Remove cover and continue to cook 30 minutes more.

title: indian tacos
directions: Brown beef; drain and add sauce and undrained kidney beans. Top Fry Bread with beef and add vegetables and cheese.

title: chocolate chip toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, stir together the flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg; mix well. Stir in the chocolate chips and nuts.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups mixture. Press remaining crumb mixture onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: Cut each slice of cheese in half.
Place each half on top of chicken cutlet.
Starting with a short end, tightly roll up cutlets jelly roll style.
Tie securely with string.
On waxed paper, combine flour and pepper.
Mix well.
Add cutlets; toss gently to coat.

title: fried rice
directions: *Cook old fashioned rice (brown or white) the day before and refrigerate.

title: warm asparagus spinach salad
directions: Place asparagus in a baking dish. Drizzle with 2 tablespoons olive oil. Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon salt. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender. Cook pasta according to package directions and drain. Combine onions, vinegar and soy sauce in blender. Gradually add 1/2 cup olive oil. Pour dressing over spinach, pasta and asparagus. Sprinkle cashews and Parmesan cheese on top. Serve immediately.

title: indonesian crab canapes
directions: Process everything except crab, scallions and mayonnaise until the peanuts are minced.
Mix with other ingredients.
Spread 1 tablespoon on each toast and bake in a preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes, or until they are browned lightly on top.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 24.

title: pineapple-coconut delight(hettie's)
directions: Cream together the sugar and oleo. Add the eggs.
Mix the pineapple, coconut and pecans; add to the creamed mixture.
Fold in the whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Line the bottom of a Pyrex dish with the vanilla wafers. Alternate with the mixture and wafers, with mixture on top. Chill overnight.

title: ka 'lachi
directions: Dip biscuits in butter, then in cinnamon-sugar.
Make hollow in center of biscuit with your thumb and fill with cream cheese. Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: turkey a la king
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large ovenproof skillet, heat oleo until bubbly.
Add mushroom and saute 2 minutes.
Stir in flour then gradually whisk in broth and milk.
Dissolve broth, 1/2 cup hot water.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients except biscuits.
Remove from heat.
Border turkey mixture with biscuits.
Bake about 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lo-cal shredded wheat pancakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.

title: grill meat sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add liquid smoke.
Seasoned salt and pepper goes on the type meat you are going to grill.
May brush meat or sprinkle while grilling.

title: no bake peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter chips and shortening in top of a double boiler over hot water.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Combine cereal, melted chips and raisins; stir until cereal is coated. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a waxed paper lined cookie sheet. Cover; chill for 1 hour.

title: hearty turkey stew
directions: Heat oil over medium-high heat in 5-quart Dutch oven, until oil sizzles.
Cut tenderloin into 1/2-inch slices.
Place turkey, potatoes, carrots, celery, onions and garlic in a pan.
Cook and stir frequently until turkey is no longer pink (about 10 minutes).

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt oleo in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish or larger.
Mix all ingredients except cheese together.
Pour in baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Can be reheated in microwave.

title: white house macaroni & cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Boil Macaroni in water.
Drain and place in buttered casserole dish.
Add Cheddar Cheese, Salt, Pepper and Ham.
Cover all with Milk.
Sprinkle crumbled Saltine Crackers over the top.
Dot top with Butter.
Bake 40 minutes. 6 - 8 servings.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Beat eggs.
Add Bisquick, oil and milk.
Mix all together with zucchini, onion and cheese.
Pour in a greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: summer tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags and mint leaves; let steep for 15 minutes.
Add undiluted frozen juices and sugar.
Mix well. Add water to make 1 gallon of summer tea.
Serves 18 - 20.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugars.
Have eggs and milk room temperature.
Add	remaining
ingredients	to
creamed mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry waldorf fluff
directions: Combine cranberries, marshmallows and sugar; mix lightly. Cover and chill.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Serves 6.

title: bacon bread sticks
directions: Cut bacon slices lengthwise ways to make 2 slices out of one. Wrap one slice of bacon around a bread stick. Do this until all bread sticks are wrapped with bacon. Place on a microwave bacon plate and cook in microwave until bacon is done. Roll bread sticks in Parmesan cheese after cooking. Serve as a party snack.

title: candy apples
directions: You will need 8 wooden ice cream bar sticks.

title: pork roast
directions: Rub
roast
with
mixture
of
onion salt, marjoram and pepper.
Place
pork, fat side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan in oven.
Roast, uncovered, in a 325° oven for about 2 1/2 hours. Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour peach pie filling in a bowl.
Add other ingredients. Chill and serve.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: hopewell chicken casserole
directions: Blend soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and water chestnuts.
Spread evenly in a 9 x 9-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Combine margarine and corn flakes and sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bubble buns
directions: Grease ten 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
In a small bowl combine walnuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Separate biscuits and cut into quarters.
Shape into balls.
Coat each with mayonnaise, then roll in walnut mixture.
Place 4 balls in each muffin pan cup. Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine.
Beat in eggs and sugars.
Add vanilla.
Blend in flour, soda, salt and oats.
Stir in peanuts. Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake(or cupcakes)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; batter will be very stiff.
Add a few drops of water if necessary.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: loose meat sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients in skillet and cook on high, stirring frequently until cooked.
Serve on low-fat hamburger buns.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni meal
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Butter a casserole dish (4-quart).
Sprinkle some of the cheese on bottom and sides.
Layer mixture with cheese.
Sprinkle more cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until top is browned, about 45 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Stir thoroughly and serve.
No need to wait for it to gel.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Flatten with 1/2 pecan.
Bake at 300° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Do not overbake.
(A delicious cheese treat for your appetizer table or to accompany soup or salad.)

title: banana muffins
directions: In a bowl, mix eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon, and bananas; mix well. Work in baking mix; add nuts. Pour into greased muffin tin. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve with Lite cream cheese or cinnamon butter. Makes 12 muffins.

title: corn and cheese souffl
directions: Combine melted butter, flour, pepper, and salt in a large bowl. Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Add cheese and corn.
Stir to blend.
Beat egg yolks.
To prevent egg yolks from cooking in hard lumps when added to the cheese sauce, add a little cheese sauce to the yolks and stir well.
Then add this mixture to the bowl of cheese sauce; blending well.
Beat egg whites with an electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Fold egg whites into cheese sauce until just blended.
Pour into a buttered 2 quart souffl dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: avocado dressing
directions: Peel avocado and cut into chunks.
Blend in blender with sour cream and cream; blend briefly and then add rest of ingredients. Blend until smooth (several minutes).
Cover and chill with plastic film on surface of mixture so it will not darken.
Makes 2 cups.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix with 1 can drained shrimp and 1/3 bottle of sauce.
Form ball; pour 2/3 bottle of sauce over top. Serve with crackers.
Sure to be a party favorite.

title: chocolate or butterscotch coated peanuts
directions: Melt chocolate or butterscotch pieces in top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water. Add peanuts and stir to coat.
Turn out on waxed paper and separate with fork.
Allow to cool.

title: chocolate cream cheese fudge
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl and cream until soft and smooth. Slowly blend in sugar. Add cocoa. Mix well. Add vanilla, salt and nuts. Mix until well blended. Press into well-greased shallow pan. Place in refrigerator for 15 minutes or until firm. Cut into squares.

title: ground chuck chop suey
directions: Heat fat in a large frypan.
Add celery, onion and ground chuck and cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes or until meat begins to brown.
Blend cornstarch with water and stir into beef mixture.
Add bouillon cube, soy sauce and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened and clear. Stir in cabbage.
Cook, covered, about 3 to 8 minutes, until cabbage is tender, but still firm.
Serve on rice.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Stir well.
Spoon onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: wedding mints
directions: Divide equal amounts and roll into balls.
Work coloring into them.
Roll into small balls and put into mold coated with white sugar (granulated).
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This will make its own crust.

title: nonfat fruit drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix on high until well blended.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Peel boiled potatoes and cut into small pieces; set aside. Combine next 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Gently stir in potatoes and cheese.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine margarine and stuffing mix, then sprinkle over mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: potato croquettes(left over mashed potatoes)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
If if feels too soft, add a little more bread crumbs, but not too much as it ruins the flavor.
Put some bread crumbs in a piece of wax paper to put on the croquette before frying.
Put some oil in frypan and get it hot, while that is getting hot, make the croquette.
Wet the palms of your hand and make a patty the size you want.
Now put it in the wax paper with crumbs and coat the patty.
Place in the frypan and brown on both sides and your croquettes are ready to eat.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix garlic, bacon grease, chili powder and cornstarch together in a saucepan.
Add tomato juice, water, ketchup, sugar, salt and Tabasco.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.

title: betsy's spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry meats together.
Take out of pan.
Put in 2 cans of paste and cook.
Add to rest of sauce ingredients in other pan.
Cook slowly.

title: apple banana salad
directions: Mix fruits and all ingredients until coated.

title: world's greatest vegetable soup
directions: Use large pan, at least 6 to 8 quarts.
Fill 3/4 full.
Cook beef soup bone and as much meat as desired.
Skim scum as it rises to surface.
When scum no longer rises, add tomato sauce and onion.
Cook gently for 2 to 3 hours.
Add carrots, celery and parsley.
Cook 1 hour.
Add head of cabbage, cut in bite sized pieces and cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Stir sugar and boiling water until sugar melts.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 2 more cups sugar and 1 cup boiling water.
Add salt and vinegar.
Boil hard until soft ball stage.
Take off stove and add pecans.
Stir until it begins to slightly cream. Drop onto wax paper.

title: potato delight
directions: Combine mashed potatoes, softened cream cheese and butter. Add remaining ingredients and place in an oiled casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. This will puff slightly as it bakes. Casserole may be refrigerated or frozen and baked later. Increase baking time accordingly.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form into a ball or squares. Sprinkle with paprika. Let season in refrigerator 24 hours.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: banana bread(by mary boston)
directions: Mix sour milk with baking soda and mashed bananas.
Mix all ingredients together well. Mix bananas last.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Walnuts are optional.

title: brazil nut shortbread
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Sift flour once; measure and sift again.
Work into butter and sugar.
Blend in nuts.
Chill dough and shape into round balls, about the size of small walnuts, then flatten.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Cook onion and green peppers in boiling water until tender. Drain. Stir in tomato sauce, eggs, cheese, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and thyme.
Add ground beef, mixing well.
Shape into loaf in baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Measure corn meal and set aside.
Put water in saucepan and boil slowly.
Add meal, stirring as you add the meal.
Turn heat on low.
Add salt and cook 5 minutes.
When done, mix with milk and eat.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package instructions.
When almost set, add pineapple, cottage cheese, Cool Whip and cherries on top.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain. Slice 2 of the eggs into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. In a saucepan, melt butter. Blend in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles. Stir sausage and corn into sauce. Pour over eggs in the casserole dish. Slice the 2 remaining eggs over top of casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through. Serves 6.

title: dot webb's apple nut pudding
directions: Beat egg well; gradually add sugar and continue beating until dissolved.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add to egg mixture.
Fold in apples, walnuts and almond extract.
Bake in 8-inch square pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipping cream.
(From Pennsylvania's orchard region.)

title: ratatouille provencale
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil until golden.
Add eggplant and saute until
soft.
Remove from skillet and saute peppers, zucchini and tomatoes
until soft adding olive oil as needed.
Place in casserole
dish
with basil, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with grated
Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or
cold with sour cream or low-cal yogurt.

title: big burger
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients for dough.
Press 1/2 dough into pie tin.
Save other 1/2 dough.
Mix next 7 ingredients for filling. Pour filling into pie tin.
Roll out rest of dough in circle for top.
Place on top of pie and seal edges.
Mix last 3 ingredients and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: skillet buttermilk cornbread
directions: Mix together then add 2 eggs and buttermilk to moisten (not too thin).
Heat 2-3 tbsp. shortening or oil in a large cast iron skillet.
When shortening is hot pour in cornbread mixture.
Bake in 425 degrees until brown.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Stir in flour and continue to stir until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat; add eggs, one at a time (make sure each egg is mixed into dough before adding next one).
Spread on ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400° until golden brown.
Poke hole in bubbles and let cool.
Cream pudding and cheese; add milk and mix with electric beater.
Spread on top of crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour; cut and serve.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Mix soda with applesauce and combine with creamed mixture.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 to 3 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
This recipe may be varied by using 1 3/4 cups flour and 1 cup oatmeal.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil, pumpkin, eggs and water.
Mix together and add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool for 30 minutes before removing from pans.

title: etha belle's banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together with hamburger except cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 375° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: scalloped garden vegetables
directions: Slice vegetables and layer a casserole with squash, zucchini, tomato and onion.
Use seasonings on each layer of vegetables.
An alternate method is to combine vegetables in large bowl and mix thoroughly with seasonings.
This coats them well.
Then put in a casserole dish and drizzle with 1/4 cup butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 20 minutes.
Put Mozzarella on top and combine bread crumbs with remaining butter.
Top with Parmesan and bake, uncovered, 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: chicken cutlets in sauce
directions: Cut chicken in long pieces.
Stir-fry in a pan with cooking oil until tender and a minimum of golden color.
Cut onion in pieces.
Add to chicken; add broccoli and stir-fry together.
Mix cornstarch in 1/4 cup of the water.
Boil water left; add chicken bouillon cube until dissolved.
Stir again to mix the cornstarch with water and add to the chicken bouillon until cooked, stirring constantly.
Add to chicken cutlets.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 3 ingredients.
Sift together the flour and salt and stir in.
Mix in the chopped nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased pan (cookies do not spread).
Bake until set, but not brown.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Roll in sugar again.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen 1-inch cookies.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine, then saute onions, pepper and mushroom together.
Add mixture to rice.
Add consomme last.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tiptop cake
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and flavoring.
Beat thoroughly after each addition.
Makes 2 (8-inch) layers or 1 (3 1/2 x 8 x 4-inch) loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for layers and 45 minutes for loaf.
I use this cake when I need to bake something quick.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots in boiling salted water for 10 to 15 minutes; drain.
In saucepan, mix brown sugar, cornstarch, ginger and salt.
Stir in orange juice; cook and stir until mixture is thickened.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in butter.
Toss with hot carrots.
Top with parsley and an orange slice, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: santa fe bean dip
directions: In a crock-pot mix all ingredients and heat on low.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Cut bamboo shoots into strips and mushrooms into very thin slices.
Add the pear, tomatoes, and thinly sliced chicken.
Beat the eggs and leave aside.
Bring chicken stock to a boil.
Add prepared ingredients except the eggs and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add salt, sugar, sesame oil and ginger sherry and cook for 1/2 minute. Trickle beaten eggs into soup, stirring as you do.
Cook for 1/4 minute.
Serve at once.

title: overnight lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onion and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook several minutes, stirring frequently.
Drain.
In mixing bowl, combine spaghetti sauce, 1 cup water, oregano, pepper and sugar.
In another bowl, combine egg, Ricotta, Parmesan, Mozzarella and parsley.

title: taffy apples
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and cinnamon candies with 1 cup water.
Over medium heat, stir constantly, just until sugar and candies are dissolved.
Do not boil.
Add food coloring and cinnamon.
Stir to mix well.
Bring syrup to boiling. Continue cooking, without stirring, to 300° on candy thermometer.

title: holiday pork roast
directions: Melt jelly.
Add soy sauce and sherry.
Simmer 2 minutes. Serve in separate dish with roast.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well (except for pecans) and form into a ball. Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and cover top with chopped pecans.

title: cheese sausage biscuit
directions: Combine cheese and sausage.
Add Bisquick and pepper.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream until smooth. Use as a dip for fresh fruit.

title: rosie's brownies deluxe
directions: Melt in top of double boiler 2 sticks oleo and 4 squares chocolate.
In mixing bowl beat eggs; add 2 cups sugar gradually. Add sifted flour and baking powder.
Add chocolate mixture (do not wash boiler), 2 teaspoons vanilla and nutmeats.
Spread in large pan.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.
(Will pull away from edge slightly.)

title: garlic french dressing
directions: In a jar with cover, combine all ingredients.
Cover and shake well to mix.
Refrigerate.

title: icebox pickles(kosher)
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together and cool to lukewarm.
In a gallon jar place garlic cloves, bay leaves and pickling spice. Pack with fresh dill in bottom, middle and top.
Then pour on cooled mixture.
Leave out of refrigerator.
Use small pickles.
